{"term": "2004", "caseName": "Illinois v. Caballes", "caseLink": "https://www.oyez.org/cases/2004/03-923", "caseTranscripts": [{"transcriptTitle": "Oral Argument - November 10, 2004", "transcriptLink": "https://apps.oyez.org/player/#/rehnquist10/oral_argument_audio/22579", "transcript": [{"speakerName": "John Paul Stevens", "textObjs": [{"text": "We will now hear argument in Illinois against Caballes.", "start": 0, "stop": 5.739, "duration": 5.74, "cleanText": [["we", "will", "now", "hear", "argument", "in", "illinois", "against", "caballes"]]}, {"text": "General Madigan.", "start": 5.739, "stop": 6.937, "duration": 1.2, "cleanText": [["general", "madigan"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Lisa Madigan", "textObjs": [{"text": "Thank you, Justice Stevens, and may it please the Court:", "start": 6.937, "stop": 11.107, "duration": 4.17, "cleanText": [["thank", "you", "justice", "stevens", "and", "may", "it", "please", "the", "court"]]}, {"text": "This Court has made clear on several occasions, including 21 years ago in Place and 4 years ago in Edmond, that a sniff by a drug-detection dog is not a Fourth Amendment search, and if something is neither a search nor a seizure, then it requires no Fourth Amendment justification.", "start": 11.107, "stop": 30.881, "duration": 19.77, "cleanText": [["this", "court", "have", "make", "clear", "on", "several", "occasion", "include", "year", "ago", "in", "place", "and", "year", "ago", "in", "edmond", "that", "a", "sniff", "by", "a", "drug", "detection", "dog", "be", "not", "a", "fourth", "amendment", "search", "and", "if", "something", "be", "neither", "a", "search", "nor", "a", "seizure", "then", "it", "require", "no", "fourth", "amendment", "justification"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "David H. Souter", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, we've held that it's certainly not a... a full-blown search.", "start": 30.881, "stop": 34.884, "duration": 4, "cleanText": [["well", "we", "have", "hold", "that", "it", "be", "certainly", "not", "a", "a", "full", "blown", "search"]]}, {"text": "It's not a search in the classic sense, but a Terry stop isn't an arrest in... in the classic sense either.", "start": 34.884, "stop": 41.822, "duration": 6.94, "cleanText": [["it", "be", "not", "a", "search", "in", "the", "classic", "sense", "but", "a", "terry", "stop", "be", "not", "an", "arrest", "in", "in", "the", "classic", "sense", "either"]]}, {"text": "We... we have said that that is a kind of seizure.", "start": 41.822, "stop": 44.438, "duration": 2.62, "cleanText": [["we", "we", "have", "say", "that", "that", "be", "a", "kind", "of", "seizure"]]}, {"text": "Why do... I think your... your argument assumes that this for... for purposes of search analogies that something is either a... a full-dress search or it's not a search at all.", "start": 44.438, "stop": 57.713, "duration": 13.27, "cleanText": [["why", "do", "i", "think", "your", "your", "argument", "assume", "that", "this", "for", "for", "purpose", "of", "search", "analogy", "that", "something", "be", "either", "a", "a", "full", "dress", "search", "or", "it", "be", "not", "a", "search", "at", "all"]]}, {"text": "Why isn't there a... a possibility of... of a kind of middle ground searches just as there is on seizures?", "start": 57.713, "stop": 65.803, "duration": 8.09, "cleanText": [["why", "be", "not", "there", "a", "a", "possibility", "of", "of", "a", "kind", "of", "middle", "ground", "search", "just", "as", "there", "be", "on", "seizure"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Lisa Madigan", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, this Court made clear in Arizona v. Hicks that it did not want to go down the road of creating something known as a quasi-search so that courts and police officers would be in the position of trying to determine whether or not something was a search or not.", "start": 65.803, "stop": 83.059, "duration": 17.26, "cleanText": [["well", "this", "court", "make", "clear", "in", "arizona", "v", "hick", "that", "it", "do", "not", "want", "to", "go", "down", "the", "road", "of", "create", "something", "know", "as", "a", "quasi", "search", "so", "that", "court", "and", "police", "officer", "would", "be", "in", "the", "position", "of", "try", "to", "determine", "whether", "or", "not", "something", "be", "a", "search", "or", "not"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "David H. Souter", "textObjs": [{"text": "Oh, I... I can... I can just imagine the problems, but I mean, what... I think what's... what the... what's bothering me about the case is that if we persist in... in saying that... that it's... that it's an either and or question with no question with no possible gradation, then I assume nothing prevents the police from taking the dogs through every municipal garage in the United States and I suppose there's nothing that prevents the police from taking the dogs up to any homeowner's door, ringing the bell, and seeing if the dog gets a sniff of something when the door is opened.", "start": 83.059, "stop": 121.985, "duration": 38.93, "cleanText": [["oh", "i", "i", "can", "i", "can", "just", "imagine", "the", "problem", "but", "i", "mean", "what", "i", "think", "what", "be", "what", "the", "what", "be", "bother", "me", "about", "the", "case", "be", "that", "if", "we", "persist", "in", "in", "say", "that", "that", "it", "be", "that", "it", "be", "an", "either", "and", "or", "question", "with", "no", "question", "with", "no", "possible", "gradation", "then", "i", "assume", "nothing", "prevent", "the", "police", "from", "take", "the", "dog", "through", "every", "municipal", "garage", "in", "the", "united", "state", "and", "i", "suppose", "there", "be", "nothing", "that", "prevent", "the", "police", "from", "take", "the", "dog", "up", "to", "any", "homeowner", "s", "door", "ring", "the", "bell", "and", "see", "if", "the", "dog", "get", "a", "sniff", "of", "something", "when", "the", "door", "be", "open"]]}, {"text": "We're... we're opening rather a... a large vista for... for dog intrusions, and... and that's what's... that's what's bothering me.", "start": 121.985, "stop": 130.985, "duration": 9, "cleanText": [["we", "be", "we", "be", "open", "rather", "a", "a", "large", "vista", "for", "for", "dog", "intrusion", "and", "and", "that", "be", "what", "be", "that", "be", "what", "be", "bother", "me"]]}, {"text": "Why... why should we... why should we open that vista if there is a possibility of a... of a middle ground that would prevent it?", "start": 130.985, "stop": 137.672, "duration": 6.69, "cleanText": [["why", "why", "should", "we", "why", "should", "we", "open", "that", "vista", "if", "there", "be", "a", "possibility", "of", "a", "of", "a", "middle", "ground", "that", "would", "prevent", "it"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Lisa Madigan", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, I would start with the reality that dog sniffs by their very nature, as this Court recognized in both Place and Edmond, are very unique both in terms of the manner in which the sniff is conducted, as well as the content of... of the information that the sniff reveals, so that a dog sniff is only going to be able to reveal the presence or absence of contraband.", "start": 137.672, "stop": 165.082, "duration": 27.41, "cleanText": [["well", "i", "would", "start", "with", "the", "reality", "that", "dog", "sniff", "by", "their", "very", "nature", "as", "this", "court", "recognize", "in", "both", "place", "and", "edmond", "be", "very", "unique", "both", "in", "term", "of", "the", "manner", "in", "which", "the", "sniff", "be", "conduct", "as", "well", "as", "the", "content", "of", "of", "the", "information", "that", "the", "sniff", "reveals", "so", "that", "a", "dog", "sniff", "be", "only", "go", "to", "be", "able", "to", "reveal", "the", "presence", "or", "absence", "of", "contraband"]]}, {"text": "And this Court has recognized that individuals have no privacy interest in the possession of contraband.", "start": 165.082, "stop": 171.936, "duration": 6.85, "cleanText": [["and", "this", "court", "have", "recognize", "that", "individual", "have", "no", "privacy", "interest", "in", "the", "possession", "of", "contraband"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Ruth Bader Ginsburg", "textObjs": [{"text": "Does that imply that your answer is yes to the question?", "start": 171.936, "stop": 176.394, "duration": 4.46, "cleanText": [["do", "that", "imply", "that", "your", "answer", "be", "yes", "to", "the", "question"]]}, {"text": "If we say, as you urge, a dog sniff is not a search, then the police are free to parade up and down every street in the country with dogs sniffing car trunks.", "start": 176.394, "stop": 190.633, "duration": 14.24, "cleanText": [["if", "we", "say", "as", "you", "urge", "a", "dog", "sniff", "be", "not", "a", "search", "then", "the", "police", "be", "free", "to", "parade", "up", "and", "down", "every", "street", "in", "the", "country", "with", "dog", "sniff", "car", "trunk"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Lisa Madigan", "textObjs": [{"text": "Yes.", "start": 190.633, "stop": 191.627, "duration": 0.99, "cleanText": [["yes"]]}, {"text": "Because a sniff is not a search, a police officer would be able to take a narcotics-detection dog down the street with him or her.", "start": 191.627, "stop": 198.973, "duration": 7.35, "cleanText": [["because", "a", "sniff", "be", "not", "a", "search", "a", "police", "officer", "would", "be", "able", "to", "take", "a", "narcotic", "detection", "dog", "down", "the", "street", "with", "him", "or", "her"]]}, {"text": "I can tell you that because of the limited resources... and this is a point brought up in the Illinois Association of Chiefs of Police amicus brief... that that is not likely to occur.", "start": 198.973, "stop": 209.459, "duration": 10.49, "cleanText": [["i", "can", "tell", "you", "that", "because", "of", "the", "limited", "resource", "and", "this", "be", "a", "point", "bring", "up", "in", "the", "illinois", "association", "of", "chief", "of", "police", "amicus", "brief", "that", "that", "be", "not", "likely", "to", "occur"]]}, {"text": "In addition, I can also tell you that in the State of Illinois, the Illinois State police do not train their dogs nor do they use their dogs on people.", "start": 209.459, "stop": 219.035, "duration": 9.58, "cleanText": [["in", "addition", "i", "can", "also", "tell", "you", "that", "in", "the", "state", "of", "illinois", "the", "illinois", "state", "police", "do", "not", "train", "their", "dog", "nor", "do", "they", "use", "their", "dog", "on", "people"]]}, {"text": "They only use them on objects.", "start": 219.035, "stop": 220.727, "duration": 1.69, "cleanText": [["they", "only", "use", "them", "on", "object"]]}, {"text": "But yes, in answer to both of your questions, because a dog sniff does not constitute a search, dogs could be used to walk down streets.", "start": 220.727, "stop": 230.758, "duration": 10.03, "cleanText": [["but", "yes", "in", "answer", "to", "both", "of", "your", "question", "because", "a", "dog", "sniff", "do", "not", "constitute", "a", "search", "dog", "could", "be", "use", "to", "walk", "down", "street"]]}, {"text": "They could, hypothetically, be used in parking lots, and at times they are used in parking lots.", "start": 230.758, "stop": 235.466, "duration": 4.71, "cleanText": [["they", "could", "hypothetically", "be", "use", "in", "park", "lot", "and", "at", "time", "they", "be", "use", "in", "park", "lot"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Antonin Scalia", "textObjs": [{"text": "But they are used.", "start": 235.466, "stop": 236.042, "duration": 0.58, "cleanText": [["but", "they", "be", "use"]]}, {"text": "I mean, we don't have to make it up.", "start": 236.042, "stop": 236.868, "duration": 0.83, "cleanText": [["i", "mean", "we", "do", "not", "have", "to", "make", "it", "up"]]}, {"text": "From cases we've had here, we know that they're used in places like bus depots to... to sniff luggage that... that passengers have carried through on... on buses.", "start": 236.868, "stop": 248.302, "duration": 11.43, "cleanText": [["from", "case", "we", "have", "have", "here", "we", "know", "that", "they", "be", "use", "in", "place", "like", "bus", "depot", "to", "to", "sniff", "luggage", "that", "that", "passenger", "have", "carry", "through", "on", "on", "bus"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Lisa Madigan", "textObjs": [{"text": "Yes, they are.", "start": 248.302, "stop": 249.5, "duration": 1.2, "cleanText": [["yes", "they", "be"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Antonin Scalia", "textObjs": [{"text": "And the republic seems to have survived.", "start": 249.5, "stop": 251.275, "duration": 1.78, "cleanText": [["and", "the", "republic", "seem", "to", "have", "survive"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Lisa Madigan", "textObjs": [{"text": "I agree.", "start": 251.275, "stop": 252.844, "duration": 1.57, "cleanText": [["i", "agree"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Ruth Bader Ginsburg", "textObjs": [{"text": "One could characterize those episodes under the, quote, special needs doctrine.", "start": 252.844, "stop": 258.788, "duration": 5.94, "cleanText": [["one", "could", "characterize", "those", "episode", "under", "the", "quote", "special", "need", "doctrine"]]}, {"text": "I mean, we are exposed to searches at airports that we would not put up with walking up and down an ordinary street.", "start": 258.788, "stop": 267.212, "duration": 8.42, "cleanText": [["i", "mean", "we", "be", "expose", "to", "search", "at", "airport", "that", "we", "would", "not", "put", "up", "with", "walk", "up", "and", "down", "an", "ordinary", "street"]]}, {"text": "So the dogs at the terminals one expects nowadays.", "start": 267.212, "stop": 271.42, "duration": 4.21, "cleanText": [["so", "the", "dog", "at", "the", "terminal", "one", "expect", "nowadays"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Antonin Scalia", "textObjs": [{"text": "No.", "start": 271.42, "stop": 273.072, "duration": 1.65, "cleanText": [["no"]]}, {"text": "These aren't sniffs for... for explosives.", "start": 273.072, "stop": 275.218, "duration": 2.15, "cleanText": [["these", "be", "not", "sniff", "for", "for", "explosive"]]}, {"text": "These are sniffs for drugs and... and these... these are not buses that are coming in from France.", "start": 275.218, "stop": 280.419, "duration": 5.2, "cleanText": [["these", "be", "sniff", "for", "drug", "and", "and", "these", "these", "be", "not", "bus", "that", "be", "come", "in", "from", "france"]]}, {"text": "They're coming in from one American city to another.", "start": 280.419, "stop": 283.103, "duration": 2.68, "cleanText": [["they", "be", "come", "in", "from", "one", "american", "city", "to", "another"]]}, {"text": "And... and there's no more need in... in that case than there was in this case.", "start": 283.103, "stop": 288.138, "duration": 5.03, "cleanText": [["and", "and", "there", "be", "no", "more", "need", "in", "in", "that", "case", "than", "there", "be", "in", "this", "case"]]}, {"text": "It was just a good... a good place to find criminals who were carrying unlawful drugs.", "start": 288.138, "stop": 294.044, "duration": 5.91, "cleanText": [["it", "be", "just", "a", "good", "a", "good", "place", "to", "find", "criminal", "who", "we", "be", "carry", "unlawful", "drug"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Lisa Madigan", "textObjs": [{"text": "In the present case, Mr. Caballes was traveling from Las Vegas, Nevada apparently on his way to Chicago, Illinois.", "start": 294.044, "stop": 302.422, "duration": 8.38, "cleanText": [["in", "the", "present", "case", "mr", "caballes", "be", "travel", "from", "la", "vega", "nevada", "apparently", "on", "his", "way", "to", "chicago", "illinois"]]}, {"text": "He was pulled over for speeding.", "start": 302.422, "stop": 304.197, "duration": 1.77, "cleanText": [["he", "be", "pull", "over", "for", "speeding"]]}, {"text": "Another officer overheard when Master Sergeant Gillette called in to dispatch that he effected--", "start": 304.197, "stop": 312.659, "duration": 8.46, "cleanText": [["another", "officer", "overheard", "when", "master", "sergeant", "gillette", "call", "in", "to", "dispatch", "that", "he", "effect"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "John Paul Stevens", "textObjs": [{"text": "May I interrupt, General Madigan?", "start": 312.659, "stop": 314.6, "duration": 1.94, "cleanText": [["may", "i", "interrupt", "general", "madigan"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Lisa Madigan", "textObjs": [{"text": "--You may.", "start": 314.6, "stop": 315.055, "duration": 0.45, "cleanText": [["you", "may"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "John Paul Stevens", "textObjs": [{"text": "He was pulled over for speeding at 71 miles an hour in a 65 mile an hour zone on I-80.", "start": 315.055, "stop": 323.161, "duration": 8.11, "cleanText": [["he", "be", "pull", "over", "for", "speed", "at", "mile", "an", "hour", "in", "a", "mile", "an", "hour", "zone", "on", "i"]]}, {"text": "Right?", "start": 323.161, "stop": 323.766, "duration": 0.61, "cleanText": [["right"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Lisa Madigan", "textObjs": [{"text": "Yes, that is correct, Justice Stevens.", "start": 323.766, "stop": 325.003, "duration": 1.24, "cleanText": [["yes", "that", "be", "correct", "justice", "stevens"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "John Paul Stevens", "textObjs": [{"text": "Did they know in advance that he was someone to look for?", "start": 325.003, "stop": 327.686, "duration": 2.68, "cleanText": [["do", "they", "know", "in", "advance", "that", "he", "be", "someone", "to", "look", "for"]]}, {"text": "Because I don't imagine you arrest everybody on I-80 that goes 70 miles an hour.", "start": 327.686, "stop": 331.773, "duration": 4.09, "cleanText": [["because", "i", "do", "not", "imagine", "you", "arrest", "everybody", "on", "i", "that", "go", "mile", "an", "hour"]]}, {"text": "I've done it many times myself.", "start": 331.773, "stop": 334.085, "duration": 2.31, "cleanText": [["I", "have", "do", "it", "many", "time", "myself"]]}, {"text": "[Laughter]", "start": 334.085, "stop": 335.405, "duration": 1.32, "cleanText": [["laughter"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Antonin Scalia", "textObjs": [{"text": "Inadvertently.", "start": 335.405, "stop": 337.634, "duration": 2.23, "cleanText": [["inadvertently"]]}, {"text": "[Laughter]", "start": 337.634, "stop": 338.339, "duration": 0.7, "cleanText": [["laughter"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Lisa Madigan", "textObjs": [{"text": "We always like to have you in Illinois.", "start": 338.339, "stop": 342.258, "duration": 3.92, "cleanText": [["we", "always", "like", "to", "have", "you", "in", "illinois"]]}, {"text": "Obviously, the Illinois State Police have the ability to pull somebody over whether they're going 1 mile over the speed limit or 26 miles over the speed limit, but there is nothing in the record to indicate that they were looking for Mr. Caballes as he was traveling eastbound on I-80 towards Chicago.", "start": 342.258, "stop": 361.04, "duration": 18.78, "cleanText": [["obviously", "the", "illinois", "state", "police", "have", "the", "ability", "to", "pull", "somebody", "over", "whether", "they", "be", "go", "mile", "over", "the", "speed", "limit", "or", "mile", "over", "the", "speed", "limit", "but", "there", "be", "nothing", "in", "the", "record", "to", "indicate", "that", "they", "we", "be", "look", "for", "mr", "caballes", "as", "he", "be", "travel", "eastbound", "on", "i", "towards", "chicago"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "John Paul Stevens", "textObjs": [{"text": "Does the record tell us what time of day it was?", "start": 361.04, "stop": 362.859, "duration": 1.82, "cleanText": [["do", "the", "record", "tell", "us", "what", "time", "of", "day", "it", "be"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Lisa Madigan", "textObjs": [{"text": "Yes.", "start": 362.859, "stop": 363.352, "duration": 0.49, "cleanText": [["yes"]]}, {"text": "It was approximately 5:10 p.m.--", "start": 363.352, "stop": 365.831, "duration": 2.48, "cleanText": [["it", "be", "approximately", "pm"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "John Paul Stevens", "textObjs": [{"text": "Thank you.", "start": 365.831, "stop": 367.606, "duration": 1.77, "cleanText": [["thank", "you"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Anthony M. Kennedy", "textObjs": [{"text": "You... you answered one of the earlier questions about the possible intrusiveness of dogs everywhere by saying, well, you don't have a privacy interest in contraband, but that's never true.", "start": 367.606, "stop": 379.866, "duration": 12.26, "cleanText": [["you", "you", "answer", "one", "of", "the", "early", "question", "about", "the", "possible", "intrusiveness", "of", "dog", "everywhere", "by", "say", "well", "you", "do", "not", "have", "a", "privacy", "interest", "in", "contraband", "but", "that", "be", "never", "true"]]}, {"text": "You don't have a privacy interest in the murder victim's body, but you still have to have a warrant to go in and get it.", "start": 379.866, "stop": 387.008, "duration": 7.14, "cleanText": [["you", "do", "not", "have", "a", "privacy", "interest", "in", "the", "murder", "victim", "s", "body", "but", "you", "still", "have", "to", "have", "a", "warrant", "to", "go", "in", "and", "get", "it"]]}, {"text": "So that... that just doesn't work unless I missed something.", "start": 387.008, "stop": 389.237, "duration": 2.23, "cleanText": [["so", "that", "that", "just", "do", "not", "work", "unless", "i", "miss", "something"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Lisa Madigan", "textObjs": [{"text": "--You do not have a privacy interest in contraband, as this Court has recognized in the Jacobsen case.", "start": 389.237, "stop": 395.841, "duration": 6.6, "cleanText": [["you", "do", "not", "have", "a", "privacy", "interest", "in", "contraband", "as", "this", "court", "have", "recognize", "in", "the", "jacobsen", "case"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Anthony M. Kennedy", "textObjs": [{"text": "Yes, but you have a privacy interest in your person and in your place, and that's what we're talking about.", "start": 395.841, "stop": 399.556, "duration": 3.71, "cleanText": [["yes", "but", "you", "have", "a", "privacy", "interest", "in", "your", "person", "and", "in", "your", "place", "and", "that", "be", "what", "we", "be", "talk", "about"]]}, {"text": "So that seems to me that that just doesn't help us.", "start": 399.556, "stop": 401.99, "duration": 2.43, "cleanText": [["so", "that", "seem", "to", "me", "that", "that", "just", "do", "not", "help", "us"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Lisa Madigan", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, there is a distinction that's made in terms of Fourth Amendment protections that are given to homes and people versus cars.", "start": 401.99, "stop": 409.338, "duration": 7.35, "cleanText": [["well", "there", "be", "a", "distinction", "that", "be", "make", "in", "term", "of", "fourth", "amendment", "protection", "that", "be", "give", "to", "home", "and", "people", "versus", "car"]]}, {"text": "Ever since the Carroll case, it has been recognized that a warrantless search of a car can be done if they found probable cause.", "start": 409.338, "stop": 418.132, "duration": 8.79, "cleanText": [["ever", "since", "the", "carroll", "case", "it", "have", "be", "recognize", "that", "a", "warrantless", "search", "of", "a", "car", "can", "be", "do", "if", "they", "find", "probable", "because"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Anthony M. Kennedy", "textObjs": [{"text": "But that's because of the nature of the place being searched not because of the nature of what you're searching for.", "start": 418.132, "stop": 422.013, "duration": 3.88, "cleanText": [["but", "that", "be", "because", "of", "the", "nature", "of", "the", "place", "be", "search", "not", "because", "of", "the", "nature", "of", "what", "you", "be", "search", "for"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Lisa Madigan", "textObjs": [{"text": "Correct.", "start": 422.013, "stop": 424.037, "duration": 2.02, "cleanText": [["correct"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Antonin Scalia", "textObjs": [{"text": "Not necessarily.", "start": 424.037, "stop": 424.78, "duration": 0.74, "cleanText": [["not", "necessarily"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Anthony M. Kennedy", "textObjs": [{"text": "So it just can't be that... so the fact that you don't have a privacy interest in contraband, it doesn't seem to me... I... I don't think you need that argument.", "start": 424.78, "stop": 431.8, "duration": 7.02, "cleanText": [["so", "it", "just", "can", "not", "be", "that", "so", "the", "fact", "that", "you", "do", "not", "have", "a", "privacy", "interest", "in", "contraband", "it", "do", "not", "seem", "to", "me", "i", "i", "do", "not", "think", "you", "need", "that", "argument"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Antonin Scalia", "textObjs": [{"text": "I think you should use it.", "start": 431.8, "stop": 433.779, "duration": 1.98, "cleanText": [["i", "think", "you", "should", "use", "it"]]}, {"text": "[Laughter]", "start": 433.779, "stop": 434.606, "duration": 0.83, "cleanText": [["laughter"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Lisa Madigan", "textObjs": [{"text": "I... I plan on continuing to use it.", "start": 434.606, "stop": 437.412, "duration": 2.81, "cleanText": [["i", "i", "plan", "on", "continue", "to", "use", "it"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Antonin Scalia", "textObjs": [{"text": "Why... why do you... are you sure that Kyllo, you know, the... the imaging case, would have come out the same way if the only thing... the only thing... that the imaging could pick out is not any of the other private activities in the home, but the only thing it could possibly discern is a dead body with a knife through the heart?", "start": 437.412, "stop": 459.869, "duration": 22.46, "cleanText": [["why", "why", "do", "you", "be", "you", "sure", "that", "kyllo", "you", "know", "the", "the", "imaging", "case", "would", "have", "come", "out", "the", "same", "way", "if", "the", "only", "thing", "the", "only", "thing", "that", "the", "imaging", "could", "pick", "out", "be", "not", "any", "of", "the", "other", "private", "activity", "in", "the", "home", "but", "the", "only", "thing", "it", "could", "possibly", "discern", "be", "a", "dead", "body", "with", "a", "knife", "through", "the", "heart"]]}, {"text": "Are you sure the case would have come out the same way?", "start": 459.869, "stop": 462.554, "duration": 2.68, "cleanText": [["be", "you", "sure", "the", "case", "would", "have", "come", "out", "the", "same", "way"]]}, {"text": "I'm not at all sure.", "start": 462.554, "stop": 463.297, "duration": 0.74, "cleanText": [["I", "be", "not", "at", "all", "sure"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Lisa Madigan", "textObjs": [{"text": "I would hope the case would come out differently than--", "start": 463.297, "stop": 465.321, "duration": 2.02, "cleanText": [["i", "would", "hope", "the", "case", "would", "come", "out", "differently", "than"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Sandra Day O'Connor", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, what--", "start": 465.321, "stop": 467.262, "duration": 1.94, "cleanText": [["well", "what"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Anthony M. Kennedy", "textObjs": [{"text": "Do you have any authority for that other than Justice Scalia's speculation about how this--", "start": 467.262, "stop": 470.689, "duration": 3.43, "cleanText": [["do", "you", "have", "any", "authority", "for", "that", "other", "than", "justice", "scalia", "s", "speculation", "about", "how", "this"]]}, {"text": "[Laughter]", "start": 470.689, "stop": 471.243, "duration": 0.55, "cleanText": [["laughter"]]}, {"text": "--how his Kyllo case might have been written?", "start": 471.243, "stop": 472.835, "duration": 1.59, "cleanText": [["how", "his", "kyllo", "case", "might", "have", "be", "write"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Sandra Day O'Connor", "textObjs": [{"text": "--What about a house and... and the use of a dog to sniff around a door access or a house just because the police think, you know, it's possible this is somebody growing marijuana in the basement or something?", "start": 472.835, "stop": 489.719, "duration": 16.88, "cleanText": [["what", "about", "a", "house", "and", "and", "the", "use", "of", "a", "dog", "to", "sniff", "around", "a", "door", "access", "or", "a", "house", "just", "because", "the", "police", "think", "you", "know", "it", "be", "possible", "this", "be", "somebody", "grow", "marijuana", "in", "the", "basement", "or", "something"]]}, {"text": "Is that all right?", "start": 489.719, "stop": 491.782, "duration": 2.06, "cleanText": [["be", "that", "all", "right"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Lisa Madigan", "textObjs": [{"text": "--I would argue that, yes, it is all right to walk a dog around a house, but then as Justice--", "start": 491.782, "stop": 498.098, "duration": 6.32, "cleanText": [["i", "would", "argue", "that", "yes", "it", "be", "all", "right", "to", "walk", "a", "dog", "around", "a", "house", "but", "then", "as", "justice"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Sandra Day O'Connor", "textObjs": [{"text": "How do you... how do you reconcile that with the heat sensor case then?", "start": 498.098, "stop": 502.928, "duration": 4.83, "cleanText": [["how", "do", "you", "how", "do", "you", "reconcile", "that", "with", "the", "heat", "sensor", "case", "then"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Lisa Madigan", "textObjs": [{"text": "--The thermal imager that was used in the Kyllo case was able to reveal intimate details of the house.", "start": 502.928, "stop": 511.267, "duration": 8.34, "cleanText": [["the", "thermal", "imager", "that", "be", "use", "in", "the", "kyllo", "case", "be", "able", "to", "reveal", "intimate", "detail", "of", "the", "house"]]}, {"text": "A dog sniff is only going to reveal the presence or absence of contraband, and because of that, that's where we suddenly get into the tension between Kyllo and Place and--", "start": 511.267, "stop": 523.155, "duration": 11.89, "cleanText": [["a", "dog", "sniff", "be", "only", "go", "to", "reveal", "the", "presence", "or", "absence", "of", "contraband", "and", "because", "of", "that", "that", "be", "where", "we", "suddenly", "get", "into", "the", "tension", "between", "kyllo", "and", "place", "and"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "John Paul Stevens", "textObjs": [{"text": "What if the dogs get a little more sophisticated in the future and can also smell a certain kind of perfume, something like that?", "start": 523.155, "stop": 530.009, "duration": 6.85, "cleanText": [["what", "if", "the", "dog", "get", "a", "little", "more", "sophisticated", "in", "the", "future", "and", "can", "also", "smell", "a", "certain", "kind", "of", "perfume", "something", "like", "that"]]}, {"text": "Would then the whole analysis change?", "start": 530.009, "stop": 532.322, "duration": 2.31, "cleanText": [["would", "then", "the", "whole", "analysis", "change"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Lisa Madigan", "textObjs": [{"text": "--Well, then you would end up in a situation as to whether or not an officer had probable cause when a dog, in fact, alerted.", "start": 532.322, "stop": 540.617, "duration": 8.29, "cleanText": [["well", "then", "you", "would", "end", "up", "in", "a", "situation", "as", "to", "whether", "or", "not", "an", "officer", "have", "probable", "because", "when", "a", "dog", "in", "fact", "alert"]]}, {"text": "If he was alerting to the presence of perfume as opposed to narcotics, there--", "start": 540.617, "stop": 546.069, "duration": 5.45, "cleanText": [["if", "he", "be", "alert", "to", "the", "presence", "of", "perfume", "as", "oppose", "to", "narcotic", "there"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "John Paul Stevens", "textObjs": [{"text": "And how would you know whether the... the dog... I don't think the dog alerts, as I'm alerting, for one reason or another.", "start": 546.069, "stop": 552.506, "duration": 6.44, "cleanText": [["and", "how", "would", "you", "know", "whether", "the", "the", "dog", "i", "do", "not", "think", "the", "dog", "alert", "as", "I", "be", "alert", "for", "one", "reason", "or", "another"]]}, {"text": "He just alerts.", "start": 552.506, "stop": 553.871, "duration": 1.37, "cleanText": [["he", "just", "alert"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Lisa Madigan", "textObjs": [{"text": "--Well, they're very well trained dogs.", "start": 553.871, "stop": 556.1, "duration": 2.23, "cleanText": [["well", "they", "be", "very", "well", "trained", "dog"]]}, {"text": "In fact, in the State of Illinois, the dogs and their handlers go through 320 hours of training, and they're specifically trained to only alert to narcotics.", "start": 556.1, "stop": 566.335, "duration": 10.24, "cleanText": [["in", "fact", "in", "the", "state", "of", "illinois", "the", "dog", "and", "their", "handler", "go", "through", "hour", "of", "training", "and", "they", "be", "specifically", "train", "to", "only", "alert", "to", "narcotic"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "John Paul Stevens", "textObjs": [{"text": "I just learned this morning that some very well trained dogs that are trained to alert for explosives will also alert for certain kinds of rubber in a tire.", "start": 566.335, "stop": 575.334, "duration": 9, "cleanText": [["i", "just", "learn", "this", "morning", "that", "some", "very", "well", "trained", "dog", "that", "be", "train", "to", "alert", "for", "explosive", "will", "also", "alert", "for", "certain", "kind", "of", "rubber", "in", "a", "tire"]]}, {"text": "They didn't realize that.", "start": 575.334, "stop": 576.532, "duration": 1.2, "cleanText": [["they", "do", "not", "realize", "that"]]}, {"text": "And I think it's entirely possible that dogs would... there will be false alerts by... by dogs because it's triggered by something that... that is not really anticipated.", "start": 576.532, "stop": 586.397, "duration": 9.87, "cleanText": [["and", "i", "think", "it", "be", "entirely", "possible", "that", "dog", "would", "there", "will", "be", "false", "alert", "by", "by", "dog", "because", "it", "be", "trigger", "by", "something", "that", "that", "be", "not", "really", "anticipate"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Lisa Madigan", "textObjs": [{"text": "One of the things that does take place during the training of these narcotics-detection dogs is to make sure that they are not alerting to things that are not narcotics or... I don't know exactly how the explosive training is conducted because we don't train our dogs in Illinois for explosives, but they purposely train them on narcotics not to alert to plastic wrap that is frequently the container used for narcotics, not--", "start": 586.397, "stop": 612.032, "duration": 25.63, "cleanText": [["one", "of", "the", "thing", "that", "do", "take", "place", "during", "the", "training", "of", "these", "narcotic", "detection", "dog", "be", "to", "make", "sure", "that", "they", "be", "not", "alert", "to", "thing", "that", "be", "not", "narcotic", "or", "i", "do", "not", "know", "exactly", "how", "the", "explosive", "training", "be", "conduct", "because", "we", "do", "not", "train", "our", "dog", "in", "illinois", "for", "explosive", "but", "they", "purposely", "train", "them", "on", "narcotic", "not", "to", "alert", "to", "plastic", "wrap", "that", "be", "frequently", "the", "container", "use", "for", "narcotic", "not"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "John Paul Stevens", "textObjs": [{"text": "So you would agree the analysis would be different if there could be an innocent cause of the alert as well as the contraband being the cause of the alert.", "start": 612.032, "stop": 619.545, "duration": 7.51, "cleanText": [["so", "you", "would", "agree", "the", "analysis", "would", "be", "different", "if", "there", "could", "be", "an", "innocent", "because", "of", "the", "alert", "as", "well", "as", "the", "contraband", "be", "the", "because", "of", "the", "alert"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Lisa Madigan", "textObjs": [{"text": "--It depends.", "start": 619.545, "stop": 621.941, "duration": 2.4, "cleanText": [["it", "depend"]]}, {"text": "The analysis would be different if the dog was known to or had been trained to actually alert to the non-contraband.", "start": 621.941, "stop": 630.979, "duration": 9.04, "cleanText": [["the", "analysis", "would", "be", "different", "if", "the", "dog", "be", "know", "to", "or", "have", "be", "train", "to", "actually", "alert", "to", "the", "non", "contraband"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Antonin Scalia", "textObjs": [{"text": "Or if that happened a large percentage of the time.", "start": 630.979, "stop": 634.695, "duration": 3.72, "cleanText": [["or", "if", "that", "happen", "a", "large", "percentage", "of", "the", "time"]]}, {"text": "I mean, surely you'd concede that the search is unreasonable if, for every... every one time, you... you make somebody open his bag because the dog actually smells narcotics, 99 times you make somebody open his bag because he has apples in it.", "start": 634.695, "stop": 654.014, "duration": 19.32, "cleanText": [["i", "mean", "surely", "you", "would", "concede", "that", "the", "search", "be", "unreasonable", "if", "for", "every", "every", "one", "time", "you", "you", "make", "somebody", "open", "his", "bag", "because", "the", "dog", "actually", "smell", "narcotic", "time", "you", "make", "somebody", "open", "his", "bag", "because", "he", "have", "apple", "in", "it"]]}, {"text": "I mean, wouldn't that go to the reasonableness of--", "start": 654.014, "stop": 656.986, "duration": 2.97, "cleanText": [["i", "mean", "would", "not", "that", "go", "to", "the", "reasonableness", "of"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Lisa Madigan", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, it would actually go to whether or not that dog provided... that dog's alert provided probable cause to conduct a search.", "start": 656.986, "stop": 664.954, "duration": 7.97, "cleanText": [["well", "it", "would", "actually", "go", "to", "whether", "or", "not", "that", "dog", "provide", "that", "dog", "s", "alert", "provide", "probable", "because", "to", "conduct", "a", "search"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Anthony M. Kennedy", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, do we... we don't have the probable cause question before us, do we?", "start": 664.954, "stop": 667.433, "duration": 2.48, "cleanText": [["well", "do", "we", "we", "do", "not", "have", "the", "probable", "because", "question", "before", "us", "do", "we"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Lisa Madigan", "textObjs": [{"text": "You do not have the probable cause question before you.", "start": 667.433, "stop": 670.527, "duration": 3.09, "cleanText": [["you", "do", "not", "have", "the", "probable", "because", "question", "before", "you"]]}, {"text": "This dog was determined to be reliable by the trial court and the Illinois Appellate Court, and it was not part of the Illinois Supreme Court's decision.", "start": 670.527, "stop": 680.186, "duration": 9.66, "cleanText": [["this", "dog", "be", "determine", "to", "be", "reliable", "by", "the", "trial", "court", "and", "the", "illinois", "appellate", "court", "and", "it", "be", "not", "part", "of", "the", "illinois", "supreme", "court", "s", "decision"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Stephen G. Breyer", "textObjs": [{"text": "What again in your view is the best distinction from Kyllo?", "start": 680.186, "stop": 684.067, "duration": 3.88, "cleanText": [["what", "again", "in", "your", "view", "be", "the", "best", "distinction", "from", "kyllo"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Lisa Madigan", "textObjs": [{"text": "Two things.", "start": 684.067, "stop": 685.842, "duration": 1.77, "cleanText": [["two", "thing"]]}, {"text": "One, the thermal imager used in Kyllo was able to reveal intimate details that individuals--", "start": 685.842, "stop": 692.158, "duration": 6.32, "cleanText": [["one", "the", "thermal", "imager", "use", "in", "kyllo", "be", "able", "to", "reveal", "intimate", "detail", "that", "individual"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Sandra Day O'Connor", "textObjs": [{"text": "Like what?", "start": 692.158, "stop": 692.901, "duration": 0.74, "cleanText": [["like", "what"]]}, {"text": "I thought it was just heat?", "start": 692.901, "stop": 694.015, "duration": 1.11, "cleanText": [["i", "think", "it", "be", "just", "heat"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Antonin Scalia", "textObjs": [{"text": "--Yes.", "start": 694.015, "stop": 694.759, "duration": 0.74, "cleanText": [["yes"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Lisa Madigan", "textObjs": [{"text": "--There was some disagreement on the Court about exactly what it revealed, but in terms of intimate details, it then allowed somebody--", "start": 694.759, "stop": 702.561, "duration": 7.8, "cleanText": [["there", "be", "some", "disagreement", "on", "the", "court", "about", "exactly", "what", "it", "reveal", "but", "in", "term", "of", "intimate", "detail", "it", "then", "allow", "somebody"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Sandra Day O'Connor", "textObjs": [{"text": "Excuse me.", "start": 702.561, "stop": 702.894, "duration": 0.33, "cleanText": [["excuse", "me"]]}, {"text": "What details?", "start": 702.894, "stop": 704.047, "duration": 1.15, "cleanText": [["what", "detail"]]}, {"text": "It is a device that measures heat.", "start": 704.047, "stop": 706.998, "duration": 2.95, "cleanText": [["it", "be", "a", "device", "that", "measure", "heat"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Lisa Madigan", "textObjs": [{"text": "--Because it could measure heat, it could also potentially determine when somebody was taking a bath, taking a sauna, and doing other intimate things in the house.", "start": 706.998, "stop": 717.505, "duration": 10.51, "cleanText": [["because", "it", "could", "measure", "heat", "it", "could", "also", "potentially", "determine", "when", "somebody", "be", "take", "a", "bath", "take", "a", "sauna", "and", "do", "other", "intimate", "thing", "in", "the", "house"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Ruth Bader Ginsburg", "textObjs": [{"text": "I think there was a reference to my lady's bath in the opinion.", "start": 717.505, "stop": 721.47, "duration": 3.97, "cleanText": [["i", "think", "there", "be", "a", "reference", "to", "my", "lady", "s", "bath", "in", "the", "opinion"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Antonin Scalia", "textObjs": [{"text": "A nice turn of phrase, as I recall.", "start": 721.47, "stop": 723.616, "duration": 2.15, "cleanText": [["a", "nice", "turn", "of", "phrase", "as", "i", "recall"]]}, {"text": "[Laughter]", "start": 723.616, "stop": 724.109, "duration": 0.49, "cleanText": [["laughter"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Stephen G. Breyer", "textObjs": [{"text": "What was... and what was the second?", "start": 724.109, "stop": 726.504, "duration": 2.39, "cleanText": [["what", "be", "and", "what", "be", "the", "second"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Lisa Madigan", "textObjs": [{"text": "The second one would be the distinction between houses and cars and the protections that houses are given under the Fourth Amendment, which are far greater than the protections that people have in their cars.", "start": 726.504, "stop": 736.741, "duration": 10.24, "cleanText": [["the", "second", "one", "would", "be", "the", "distinction", "between", "house", "and", "car", "and", "the", "protection", "that", "house", "be", "give", "under", "the", "fourth", "amendment", "which", "be", "far", "great", "than", "the", "protection", "that", "people", "have", "in", "their", "car"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Anthony M. Kennedy", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, so you think if this were a house, that the Kyllo case would apply?", "start": 736.741, "stop": 739.22, "duration": 2.48, "cleanText": [["well", "so", "you", "think", "if", "this", "we", "be", "a", "house", "that", "the", "kyllo", "case", "would", "apply"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Lisa Madigan", "textObjs": [{"text": "If this were a house in the situation, it would certainly bring out the tension between Kyllo and Place--", "start": 739.22, "stop": 746.855, "duration": 7.63, "cleanText": [["if", "this", "we", "be", "a", "house", "in", "the", "situation", "it", "would", "certainly", "bring", "out", "the", "tension", "between", "kyllo", "and", "place"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Antonin Scalia", "textObjs": [{"text": "Wasn't there... didn't Kyllo... wasn't what... what the Court was worried about in Kyllo not just the relatively crude heat imaging that existed in the case before it, but the prospect of more and more sophisticated heat imaging which... which we had evidence was already in development that would enable you to see people moving around a room?", "start": 746.855, "stop": 770.344, "duration": 23.49, "cleanText": [["be", "not", "there", "do", "not", "kyllo", "be", "not", "what", "what", "the", "court", "be", "worry", "about", "in", "kyllo", "not", "just", "the", "relatively", "crude", "heat", "image", "that", "exist", "in", "the", "case", "before", "it", "but", "the", "prospect", "of", "more", "and", "more", "sophisticated", "heat", "image", "which", "which", "we", "have", "evidence", "be", "already", "in", "development", "that", "would", "enable", "you", "to", "see", "people", "move", "around", "a", "room"]]}, {"text": "I thought the case referred to that.", "start": 770.344, "stop": 771.747, "duration": 1.4, "cleanText": [["i", "think", "the", "case", "refer", "to", "that"]]}, {"text": "Now, are we going to have more and more... what's going to happen with dogs?", "start": 771.747, "stop": 776.371, "duration": 4.62, "cleanText": [["now", "be", "we", "go", "to", "have", "more", "and", "more", "what", "be", "go", "to", "happen", "with", "dog"]]}, {"text": "I... I can't imagine that... that this thing is going anywhere other than smelling narcotics and smelling bombs.", "start": 776.371, "stop": 784.107, "duration": 7.74, "cleanText": [["i", "i", "can", "not", "imagine", "that", "that", "this", "thing", "be", "go", "anywhere", "other", "than", "smell", "narcotic", "and", "smell", "bomb"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "John Paul Stevens", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, but you would argue that the same rationale should apply if, instead of using dogs, you had some sophisticated device that would buzz or ring a bell or something whenever the odor of... of narcotics was present, wouldn't you?", "start": 784.107, "stop": 798.662, "duration": 14.56, "cleanText": [["well", "but", "you", "would", "argue", "that", "the", "same", "rationale", "should", "apply", "if", "instead", "of", "use", "dog", "you", "have", "some", "sophisticated", "device", "that", "would", "buzz", "or", "ring", "a", "bell", "or", "something", "whenever", "the", "odor", "of", "of", "narcotic", "be", "present", "would", "not", "you"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Lisa Madigan", "textObjs": [{"text": "--I would argue that.", "start": 798.662, "stop": 800.065, "duration": 1.4, "cleanText": [["i", "would", "argue", "that"]]}, {"text": "So if there was an ability to create a... a mechanical dog, for instance, we would again say that the use of a mechanical dog sniff would not be a search and therefore would not--", "start": 800.065, "stop": 813.894, "duration": 13.83, "cleanText": [["so", "if", "there", "be", "an", "ability", "to", "create", "a", "a", "mechanical", "dog", "for", "instance", "we", "would", "again", "say", "that", "the", "use", "of", "a", "mechanical", "dog", "sniff", "would", "not", "be", "a", "search", "and", "therefore", "would", "not"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "John Paul Stevens", "textObjs": [{"text": "There's nothing magical about the fact that it's an animal rather than a sophisticated device.", "start": 813.894, "stop": 818.519, "duration": 4.63, "cleanText": [["there", "be", "nothing", "magical", "about", "the", "fact", "that", "it", "be", "an", "animal", "rather", "than", "a", "sophisticated", "device"]]}, {"text": "It has better detection capacity than a human being does.", "start": 818.519, "stop": 822.196, "duration": 3.68, "cleanText": [["it", "have", "good", "detection", "capacity", "than", "a", "human", "be", "do"]]}, {"text": "That's the only difference.", "start": 822.196, "stop": 823.143, "duration": 0.95, "cleanText": [["that", "be", "the", "only", "difference"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Lisa Madigan", "textObjs": [{"text": "--You are correct.", "start": 823.143, "stop": 824.342, "duration": 1.2, "cleanText": [["you", "be", "correct"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "David H. Souter", "textObjs": [{"text": "In... in discussing the... the answer to the... the Kyllo issue, you... you place an emphasis on the protection given to a house.", "start": 824.342, "stop": 834.084, "duration": 9.74, "cleanText": [["in", "in", "discuss", "the", "the", "answer", "to", "the", "the", "kyllo", "issue", "you", "you", "place", "an", "emphasis", "on", "the", "protection", "give", "to", "a", "house"]]}, {"text": "Would you go back to Justice O'Connor's question and my earlier example?", "start": 834.084, "stop": 837.632, "duration": 3.55, "cleanText": [["would", "you", "go", "back", "to", "justice", "oconnor", "s", "question", "and", "my", "early", "example"]]}, {"text": "Is it still your answer that the police can walk dogs around the foundation of the house or take a dog to the front door and ring the bell and see what it... what it sniffs when the door is opened--", "start": 837.632, "stop": 849.81, "duration": 12.18, "cleanText": [["be", "it", "still", "your", "answer", "that", "the", "police", "can", "walk", "dog", "around", "the", "foundation", "of", "the", "house", "or", "take", "a", "dog", "to", "the", "front", "door", "and", "ring", "the", "bell", "and", "see", "what", "it", "what", "it", "sniff", "when", "the", "door", "be", "open"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Lisa Madigan", "textObjs": [{"text": "I would--", "start": 849.81, "stop": 851.091, "duration": 1.28, "cleanText": [["i", "would"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "David H. Souter", "textObjs": [{"text": "--without there being a search and hence no Fourth Amendment concern?", "start": 851.091, "stop": 854.928, "duration": 3.84, "cleanText": [["without", "there", "be", "a", "search", "and", "hence", "no", "fourth", "amendment", "concern"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Lisa Madigan", "textObjs": [{"text": "--Yes, Justice Souter, I would say that that is possible because the sniff itself is not a search and it only reveals the presence or absence of contraband, which is something that the individual does not have privacy expectations--", "start": 854.928, "stop": 871.275, "duration": 16.35, "cleanText": [["yes", "justice", "souter", "i", "would", "say", "that", "that", "be", "possible", "because", "the", "sniff", "itself", "be", "not", "a", "search", "and", "it", "only", "reveal", "the", "presence", "or", "absence", "of", "contraband", "which", "be", "something", "that", "the", "individual", "do", "not", "have", "privacy", "expectation"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "David H. Souter", "textObjs": [{"text": "Okay.", "start": 871.275, "stop": 871.608, "duration": 0.33, "cleanText": [["okay"]]}, {"text": "But then... then the... then there is no significance in the house.", "start": 871.608, "stop": 874.497, "duration": 2.89, "cleanText": [["but", "then", "then", "the", "then", "there", "be", "no", "significance", "in", "the", "house"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Lisa Madigan", "textObjs": [{"text": "--There is potentially significance in the house because the--", "start": 874.497, "stop": 880.274, "duration": 5.78, "cleanText": [["there", "be", "potentially", "significance", "in", "the", "house", "because", "the"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "David H. Souter", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, when does... when does it occur?", "start": 880.274, "stop": 881.183, "duration": 0.91, "cleanText": [["well", "when", "do", "when", "do", "it", "occur"]]}, {"text": "I mean, if... if... first you say the... the house is... is a matter of significance for Kyllo analysis.", "start": 881.183, "stop": 888.697, "duration": 7.51, "cleanText": [["i", "mean", "if", "if", "first", "you", "say", "the", "the", "house", "be", "be", "a", "matter", "of", "significance", "for", "kyllo", "analysis"]]}, {"text": "We're trying to draw a distinction, if there is one, between Kyllo and this, and you say they can go to the house.", "start": 888.697, "stop": 894.52, "duration": 5.82, "cleanText": [["we", "be", "try", "to", "draw", "a", "distinction", "if", "there", "be", "one", "between", "kyllo", "and", "this", "and", "you", "say", "they", "can", "go", "to", "the", "house"]]}, {"text": "They can sniff the foundations.", "start": 894.52, "stop": 896.006, "duration": 1.49, "cleanText": [["they", "can", "sniff", "the", "foundation"]]}, {"text": "They can go to the front door, et cetera.", "start": 896.006, "stop": 897.946, "duration": 1.94, "cleanText": [["they", "can", "go", "to", "the", "front", "door", "et", "cetera"]]}, {"text": "I don't see that the house, in fact, is functioning as a distinction at all.", "start": 897.946, "stop": 901.95, "duration": 4, "cleanText": [["i", "do", "not", "see", "that", "the", "house", "in", "fact", "be", "function", "as", "a", "distinction", "at", "all"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Lisa Madigan", "textObjs": [{"text": "--This Court's precedents have shown us that in fact Fourth Amendment protections are higher in the home than they are in the car.", "start": 901.95, "stop": 911.693, "duration": 9.74, "cleanText": [["this", "court", "s", "precedent", "have", "show", "us", "that", "in", "fact", "fourth", "amendment", "protection", "be", "high", "in", "the", "home", "than", "they", "be", "in", "the", "car"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "David H. Souter", "textObjs": [{"text": "Oh, I realize that, but it seems to me your basic argument, if I understand it, is there is simply no search here, and because there is no search here, it doesn't matter whether you're dealing with a house or a parking lot or a car on the road.", "start": 911.693, "stop": 923.498, "duration": 11.81, "cleanText": [["oh", "i", "realize", "that", "but", "it", "seem", "to", "me", "your", "basic", "argument", "if", "i", "understand", "it", "be", "there", "be", "simply", "no", "search", "here", "and", "because", "there", "be", "no", "search", "here", "it", "do", "not", "matter", "whether", "you", "be", "deal", "with", "a", "house", "or", "a", "parking", "lot", "or", "a", "car", "on", "the", "road"]]}, {"text": "No search is no search.", "start": 923.498, "stop": 925.067, "duration": 1.57, "cleanText": [["no", "search", "be", "no", "search"]]}, {"text": "So for purposes of... if I... I want to understand your case, and as I understand it, for purposes of your case, there is no significance in the house because there doesn't have to be.", "start": 925.067, "stop": 934.272, "duration": 9.21, "cleanText": [["so", "for", "purpose", "of", "if", "i", "i", "want", "to", "understand", "your", "case", "and", "as", "i", "understand", "it", "for", "purpose", "of", "your", "case", "there", "be", "no", "significance", "in", "the", "house", "because", "there", "do", "not", "have", "to", "be"]]}, {"text": "The question doesn't arise because there's no search.", "start": 934.272, "stop": 936.584, "duration": 2.31, "cleanText": [["the", "question", "do", "not", "arise", "because", "there", "be", "no", "search"]]}, {"text": "Is that--", "start": 936.584, "stop": 937.327, "duration": 0.74, "cleanText": [["be", "that"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Lisa Madigan", "textObjs": [{"text": "Justice Souter, that is absolutely correct.", "start": 937.327, "stop": 940.011, "duration": 2.68, "cleanText": [["justice", "souter", "that", "be", "absolutely", "correct"]]}, {"text": "A search, as far as we are concerned... and I believe it's based on the precedents of this Court... is a sniff is not a search, and therefore it requires no Fourth Amendment justification.", "start": 940.011, "stop": 952.727, "duration": 12.72, "cleanText": [["a", "search", "as", "far", "as", "we", "be", "concerned", "and", "i", "believe", "it", "be", "base", "on", "the", "precedent", "of", "this", "court", "be", "a", "sniff", "be", "not", "a", "search", "and", "therefore", "it", "require", "no", "fourth", "amendment", "justification"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Ruth Bader Ginsburg", "textObjs": [{"text": "You said there's no disturbance of one's privacy and so that distinguishes the dog sniff from some other governmental intrusions.", "start": 952.727, "stop": 965.563, "duration": 12.84, "cleanText": [["you", "say", "there", "be", "no", "disturbance", "of", "one", "s", "privacy", "and", "so", "that", "distinguish", "the", "dog", "sniff", "from", "some", "other", "governmental", "intrusion"]]}, {"text": "But dogs can be frightening, humiliating.", "start": 965.563, "stop": 973.903, "duration": 8.34, "cleanText": [["but", "dog", "can", "be", "frightening", "humiliate"]]}, {"text": "It seems to me that there is some association with the idea that I have a right to be let alone by my government and having a large dog circle my car.", "start": 973.903, "stop": 987.732, "duration": 13.83, "cleanText": [["it", "seem", "to", "me", "that", "there", "be", "some", "association", "with", "the", "idea", "that", "i", "have", "a", "right", "to", "be", "let", "alone", "by", "my", "government", "and", "have", "a", "large", "dog", "circle", "my", "car"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Lisa Madigan", "textObjs": [{"text": "There are in this country millions of dogs, many of the types of dogs that are used by narcotics detection teams, such as Labrador retrievers and shepherds, are identical to the pets that people own.", "start": 987.732, "stop": 1004.861, "duration": 17.13, "cleanText": [["there", "be", "in", "this", "country", "million", "of", "dog", "many", "of", "the", "type", "of", "dog", "that", "be", "use", "by", "narcotic", "detection", "team", "such", "as", "labrador", "retriever", "and", "shepherd", "be", "identical", "to", "the", "pet", "that", "people", "own"]]}, {"text": "We encounter them in the parks, on the streets, and I would contend that an officer cannot be in the position of making a determination as to whether or not the individual that he encounters is going to be frightened by the dog.", "start": 1004.861, "stop": 1021.208, "duration": 16.35, "cleanText": [["we", "encounter", "them", "in", "the", "park", "on", "the", "street", "and", "i", "would", "contend", "that", "an", "officer", "can", "not", "be", "in", "the", "position", "of", "make", "a", "determination", "as", "to", "whether", "or", "not", "the", "individual", "that", "he", "encounter", "be", "go", "to", "be", "frighten", "by", "the", "dog"]]}, {"text": "Mr. Justice Stevens, if I may, I'd like to reserve the remainder of my time.", "start": 1021.208, "stop": 1025.173, "duration": 3.97, "cleanText": [["mr", "justice", "stevens", "if", "i", "may", "I", "would", "like", "to", "reserve", "the", "remainder", "of", "my", "time"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "John Paul Stevens", "textObjs": [{"text": "Yes, you may save your time.", "start": 1025.173, "stop": 1025.545, "duration": 0.37, "cleanText": [["yes", "you", "may", "save", "your", "time"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Lisa Madigan", "textObjs": [{"text": "Thank you.", "start": 1025.545, "stop": 1025.999, "duration": 0.45, "cleanText": [["thank", "you"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "John Paul Stevens", "textObjs": [{"text": "Mr. Wray.", "start": 1025.999, "stop": 1034.461, "duration": 8.46, "cleanText": [["mr", "wray"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Christopher A. Wray", "textObjs": [{"text": "Justice Stevens, and may it please the Court:", "start": 1034.461, "stop": 1037.598, "duration": 3.14, "cleanText": [["justice", "stevens", "and", "may", "it", "please", "the", "court"]]}, {"text": "There's no dispute that respondent here was lawfully stopped based on probable cause.", "start": 1037.598, "stop": 1042.8, "duration": 5.2, "cleanText": [["there", "be", "no", "dispute", "that", "respondent", "here", "be", "lawfully", "stop", "base", "on", "probable", "because"]]}, {"text": "There's also no dispute that the entire stop took less than 9 minutes.", "start": 1042.8, "stop": 1046.516, "duration": 3.72, "cleanText": [["there", "be", "also", "no", "dispute", "that", "the", "entire", "stop", "take", "less", "than", "minute"]]}, {"text": "The question is whether a second officer's use of a drug dog to sniff outside of that car during those 9 minutes required some separate Fourth Amendment justification.", "start": 1046.516, "stop": 1056.918, "duration": 10.4, "cleanText": [["the", "question", "be", "whether", "a", "second", "officer", "s", "use", "of", "a", "drug", "dog", "to", "sniff", "outside", "of", "that", "car", "during", "those", "minute", "require", "some", "separate", "fourth", "amendment", "justification"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Antonin Scalia", "textObjs": [{"text": "Do you agree with... with General Madigan that it doesn't make any difference whether the... the dog is a... is a mechanical instrument or not?", "start": 1056.918, "stop": 1067.981, "duration": 11.06, "cleanText": [["do", "you", "agree", "with", "with", "general", "madigan", "that", "it", "do", "not", "make", "any", "difference", "whether", "the", "the", "dog", "be", "a", "be", "a", "mechanical", "instrument", "or", "not"]]}, {"text": "Do you agree it makes no difference?", "start": 1067.981, "stop": 1069.838, "duration": 1.86, "cleanText": [["do", "you", "agree", "it", "make", "no", "difference"]]}, {"text": "I thought that one of the... one of the points in... in the imaging case was that this was a new technology which didn't exist and that although the ordinary rules in 1791 was that there was no search unless... you know, unless you enter the house or unless you... you physically intrude upon the person's... at least the person's clothes, we made an exception to that rule because of this new technology that enabled you to find out things without having to intrude into the home or into the person.", "start": 1069.838, "stop": 1109.674, "duration": 39.84, "cleanText": [["i", "think", "that", "one", "of", "the", "one", "of", "the", "point", "in", "in", "the", "imaging", "case", "be", "that", "this", "be", "a", "new", "technology", "which", "do", "not", "exist", "and", "that", "although", "the", "ordinary", "rule", "in", "be", "that", "there", "be", "no", "search", "unless", "you", "know", "unless", "you", "enter", "the", "house", "or", "unless", "you", "you", "physically", "intrude", "upon", "the", "person", "s", "at", "least", "the", "person", "s", "clothes", "we", "make", "an", "exception", "to", "that", "rule", "because", "of", "this", "new", "technology", "that", "enable", "you", "to", "find", "out", "thing", "without", "have", "to", "intrude", "into", "the", "home", "or", "into", "the", "person"]]}, {"text": "Now, but... but this is not a new technology.", "start": 1109.674, "stop": 1113.306, "duration": 3.63, "cleanText": [["now", "but", "but", "this", "be", "not", "a", "new", "technology"]]}, {"text": "This is a dog and... and they had that ability in 1791 just as they had it today.", "start": 1113.306, "stop": 1120.736, "duration": 7.43, "cleanText": [["this", "be", "a", "dog", "and", "and", "they", "have", "that", "ability", "in", "just", "as", "they", "have", "it", "today"]]}, {"text": "And the rule that when there's no intrusion, there's no search... there's no reason to depart from that rule with respect to a dog although there would be with respect to some sophisticated new technology that would enable you to find out all sorts of things.", "start": 1120.736, "stop": 1136.257, "duration": 15.52, "cleanText": [["and", "the", "rule", "that", "when", "there", "be", "no", "intrusion", "there", "be", "no", "search", "there", "be", "no", "reason", "to", "depart", "from", "that", "rule", "with", "respect", "to", "a", "dog", "although", "there", "would", "be", "with", "respect", "to", "some", "sophisticated", "new", "technology", "that", "would", "enable", "you", "to", "find", "out", "all", "sort", "of", "thing"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Christopher A. Wray", "textObjs": [{"text": "That's correct.", "start": 1136.257, "stop": 1137.993, "duration": 1.74, "cleanText": [["that", "be", "correct"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Antonin Scalia", "textObjs": [{"text": "It seems to me you shouldn't... you shouldn't assume that... that the fact that this is a canine makes no difference.", "start": 1137.993, "stop": 1145.773, "duration": 7.78, "cleanText": [["it", "seem", "to", "me", "you", "should", "not", "you", "should", "not", "assume", "that", "that", "the", "fact", "that", "this", "be", "a", "canine", "make", "no", "difference"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "John Paul Stevens", "textObjs": [{"text": "Are you going to rely on the fact that dogs were trained to do this sort of thing back in the 18th century?", "start": 1145.773, "stop": 1151.534, "duration": 5.76, "cleanText": [["be", "you", "go", "to", "rely", "on", "the", "fact", "that", "dog", "we", "be", "train", "to", "do", "this", "sort", "of", "thing", "back", "in", "the", "th", "century"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Christopher A. Wray", "textObjs": [{"text": "I'm going to rely on... on three distinctions between this case and Kyllo, Justice Stevens.", "start": 1151.534, "stop": 1156.652, "duration": 5.12, "cleanText": [["I", "be", "go", "to", "rely", "on", "on", "three", "distinction", "between", "this", "case", "and", "kyllo", "justice", "stevens"]]}, {"text": "The first is that the three points that the Court looked at in Kyllo were: one, as has already been referenced, the fact that it's a home, the most sacred place under the Fourth Amendment; second, that it revealed certain intimate details; and third, that that was a technology--", "start": 1156.652, "stop": 1173.249, "duration": 16.6, "cleanText": [["the", "first", "be", "that", "the", "three", "point", "that", "the", "court", "look", "at", "in", "kyllo", "we", "be", "one", "as", "have", "already", "be", "reference", "the", "fact", "that", "it", "be", "a", "home", "the", "most", "sacred", "place", "under", "the", "fourth", "amendment", "second", "that", "it", "reveal", "certain", "intimate", "detail", "and", "third", "that", "that", "be", "a", "technology"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "John Paul Stevens", "textObjs": [{"text": "It was potentially revealed.", "start": 1173.249, "stop": 1174.939, "duration": 1.69, "cleanText": [["it", "be", "potentially", "reveal"]]}, {"text": "It did not actually reveal any details.", "start": 1174.939, "stop": 1177.418, "duration": 2.48, "cleanText": [["it", "do", "not", "actually", "reveal", "any", "detail"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Christopher A. Wray", "textObjs": [{"text": "--As... as General Madigan referenced, there is obviously some disagreement within the Court on that issue, but the... the fact was that the technology in Kyllo revealed information about heat in the house which could be thought to reveal intimate details about the house.", "start": 1177.418, "stop": 1193.143, "duration": 15.73, "cleanText": [["as", "as", "general", "madigan", "reference", "there", "be", "obviously", "some", "disagreement", "within", "the", "court", "on", "that", "issue", "but", "the", "the", "fact", "be", "that", "the", "technology", "in", "kyllo", "reveal", "information", "about", "heat", "in", "the", "house", "which", "could", "be", "think", "to", "reveal", "intimate", "detail", "about", "the", "house"]]}, {"text": "The third point in Kyllo, which I think Justice Scalia is referring to, is that that was technology that was not in general public use.", "start": 1193.143, "stop": 1199.914, "duration": 6.77, "cleanText": [["the", "third", "point", "in", "kyllo", "which", "i", "think", "justice", "scalia", "be", "refer", "to", "be", "that", "that", "be", "technology", "that", "be", "not", "in", "general", "public", "use"]]}, {"text": "Dogs have been used by law enforcement across the country since Place and before to sniff everything from--", "start": 1199.914, "stop": 1207.139, "duration": 7.22, "cleanText": [["dog", "have", "be", "use", "by", "law", "enforcement", "across", "the", "country", "since", "place", "and", "before", "to", "sniff", "everything", "from"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "John Paul Stevens", "textObjs": [{"text": "But not in 1790.", "start": 1207.139, "stop": 1208.132, "duration": 0.99, "cleanText": [["but", "not", "in"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Christopher A. Wray", "textObjs": [{"text": "--Not--", "start": 1208.132, "stop": 1210.937, "duration": 2.8, "cleanText": [["not"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Anthony M. Kennedy", "textObjs": [{"text": "Did you come here--", "start": 1210.937, "stop": 1211.597, "duration": 0.66, "cleanText": [["do", "you", "come", "here"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Antonin Scalia", "textObjs": [{"text": "You don't know that, do you?", "start": 1211.597, "stop": 1212.219, "duration": 0.62, "cleanText": [["you", "do", "not", "know", "that", "do", "you"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Anthony M. Kennedy", "textObjs": [{"text": "--Did you come here having researched all about dogs in 1790?", "start": 1212.219, "stop": 1215.645, "duration": 3.43, "cleanText": [["do", "you", "come", "here", "have", "research", "all", "about", "dog", "in"]]}, {"text": "[Laughter]", "start": 1215.645, "stop": 1216.221, "duration": 0.58, "cleanText": [["laughter"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Christopher A. Wray", "textObjs": [{"text": "--Justice Kennedy, I cannot, I regret to say, tell you what dogs were doing in 1790.", "start": 1216.221, "stop": 1221.256, "duration": 5.04, "cleanText": [["justice", "kennedy", "i", "can", "not", "i", "regret", "to", "say", "tell", "you", "what", "dogs", "we", "be", "do", "in"]]}, {"text": "I can tell you... and this is maybe a factual thing that might be of interest to the Court... that the dogs who train... who are trained to alert to detect things... it's not that they are sniffing things that all dogs can't already smell.", "start": 1221.256, "stop": 1234.797, "duration": 13.54, "cleanText": [["i", "can", "tell", "you", "and", "this", "be", "maybe", "a", "factual", "thing", "that", "might", "be", "of", "interest", "to", "the", "court", "that", "the", "dog", "who", "train", "who", "be", "train", "to", "alert", "to", "detect", "thing", "it", "be", "not", "that", "they", "be", "sniff", "thing", "that", "all", "dog", "can", "not", "already", "smell"]]}, {"text": "It's rather that they are trained to let the handler know that they've smelt whatever it is they've been trained to smell.", "start": 1234.797, "stop": 1240.454, "duration": 5.66, "cleanText": [["it", "be", "rather", "that", "they", "be", "train", "to", "let", "the", "handler", "know", "that", "they", "have", "smelt", "whatever", "it", "be", "they", "have", "be", "train", "to", "smell"]]}, {"text": "So the smells that are coming out of Respondent Caballes' car are exposed to every dog.", "start": 1240.454, "stop": 1245.905, "duration": 5.45, "cleanText": [["so", "the", "smell", "that", "be", "come", "out", "of", "respondent", "caballes", "car", "be", "expose", "to", "every", "dog"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "John Paul Stevens", "textObjs": [{"text": "But do you really think this would be a different case if the officer had a device that did exactly what the dog... dog did?", "start": 1245.905, "stop": 1250.985, "duration": 5.08, "cleanText": [["but", "do", "you", "really", "think", "this", "would", "be", "a", "different", "case", "if", "the", "officer", "have", "a", "device", "that", "do", "exactly", "what", "the", "dog", "dog", "do"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Christopher A. Wray", "textObjs": [{"text": "We... our position would still be, Justice Stevens, that as long as the device only revealed, as this does--", "start": 1250.985, "stop": 1257.551, "duration": 6.57, "cleanText": [["we", "our", "position", "would", "still", "be", "justice", "stevens", "that", "as", "long", "as", "the", "device", "only", "reveal", "as", "this", "do"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "John Paul Stevens", "textObjs": [{"text": "I would think you'd take--", "start": 1257.551, "stop": 1258.294, "duration": 0.74, "cleanText": [["i", "would", "think", "you", "would", "take"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Christopher A. Wray", "textObjs": [{"text": "--the absence or presence of contraband, it would still be constitutional.", "start": 1258.294, "stop": 1260.978, "duration": 2.68, "cleanText": [["the", "absence", "or", "presence", "of", "contraband", "it", "would", "still", "be", "constitutional"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "David H. Souter", "textObjs": [{"text": "Why do you rely on the... in... in distinguishing Kyllo, why do you rely on the house if there's no search?", "start": 1260.978, "stop": 1266.839, "duration": 5.86, "cleanText": [["why", "do", "you", "rely", "on", "the", "in", "in", "distinguish", "kyllo", "why", "do", "you", "rely", "on", "the", "house", "if", "there", "be", "no", "search"]]}, {"text": "Why do you have to rely on the fact that there was a house involved there?", "start": 1266.839, "stop": 1270.637, "duration": 3.8, "cleanText": [["why", "do", "you", "have", "to", "rely", "on", "the", "fact", "that", "there", "be", "a", "house", "involve", "there"]]}, {"text": "You... you listed that as one of your three distinctions.", "start": 1270.637, "stop": 1273.155, "duration": 2.52, "cleanText": [["you", "you", "list", "that", "as", "one", "of", "your", "three", "distinction"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Christopher A. Wray", "textObjs": [{"text": "We don't believe we have to rely on it, Justice Souter.", "start": 1273.155, "stop": 1275.095, "duration": 1.94, "cleanText": [["we", "do", "not", "believe", "we", "have", "to", "rely", "on", "it", "justice", "souter"]]}, {"text": "We do believe that there were three things that were important in Kyllo.", "start": 1275.095, "stop": 1279.365, "duration": 4.27, "cleanText": [["we", "do", "believe", "that", "there", "we", "be", "three", "thing", "that", "we", "be", "important", "in", "kyllo"]]}, {"text": "The fact that it was a home was one of those things.", "start": 1279.365, "stop": 1282.071, "duration": 2.71, "cleanText": [["the", "fact", "that", "it", "be", "a", "home", "be", "one", "of", "those", "thing"]]}, {"text": "Again, the... the fact of a home, the fact that it was technology not in general public use, and--", "start": 1282.071, "stop": 1287.356, "duration": 5.29, "cleanText": [["again", "the", "the", "fact", "of", "a", "home", "the", "fact", "that", "it", "be", "technology", "not", "in", "general", "public", "use", "and"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Antonin Scalia", "textObjs": [{"text": "But that didn't go to whether it was a search or seizure.", "start": 1287.356, "stop": 1289.835, "duration": 2.48, "cleanText": [["but", "that", "do", "not", "go", "to", "whether", "it", "be", "a", "search", "or", "seizure"]]}, {"text": "I think it goes to whether it was an unreasonable search or seizure.", "start": 1289.835, "stop": 1293.3, "duration": 3.46, "cleanText": [["i", "think", "it", "go", "to", "whether", "it", "be", "an", "unreasonable", "search", "or", "seizure"]]}, {"text": "Don't you think so?", "start": 1293.3, "stop": 1293.838, "duration": 0.54, "cleanText": [["do", "not", "you", "think", "so"]]}, {"text": "That what... what might be unreasonable with respect to a home would not be unreasonable with respect to a suitcase?", "start": 1293.838, "stop": 1300.154, "duration": 6.32, "cleanText": [["that", "what", "what", "might", "be", "unreasonable", "with", "respect", "to", "a", "home", "would", "not", "be", "unreasonable", "with", "respect", "to", "a", "suitcase"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Christopher A. Wray", "textObjs": [{"text": "--Yes, Justice Scalia, that's correct.", "start": 1300.154, "stop": 1302.671, "duration": 2.52, "cleanText": [["yes", "justice", "scalia", "that", "be", "correct"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "David H. Souter", "textObjs": [{"text": "But... but your... is... is it... I understand it to be your position that there simply is no search here.", "start": 1302.671, "stop": 1307.79, "duration": 5.12, "cleanText": [["but", "but", "your", "be", "be", "it", "i", "understand", "it", "to", "be", "your", "position", "that", "there", "simply", "be", "no", "search", "here"]]}, {"text": "Period.", "start": 1307.79, "stop": 1308.244, "duration": 0.45, "cleanText": [["period"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Christopher A. Wray", "textObjs": [{"text": "That is correct, Justice Souter.", "start": 1308.244, "stop": 1309.83, "duration": 1.59, "cleanText": [["that", "be", "correct", "justice", "souter"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "David H. Souter", "textObjs": [{"text": "Because it's a dog sniff.", "start": 1309.83, "stop": 1310.906, "duration": 1.08, "cleanText": [["because", "it", "be", "a", "dog", "sniff"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Christopher A. Wray", "textObjs": [{"text": "We would... we would submit this is not a search because, as this Court recognized in both Place and Edmond... and the Jacobsen case is also significant because the Court said that the reason this is not a search, there using the dog sniff by analogy, is because it compromises no legitimate privacy interest.", "start": 1310.906, "stop": 1328.943, "duration": 18.04, "cleanText": [["we", "would", "we", "would", "submit", "this", "be", "not", "a", "search", "because", "as", "this", "court", "recognize", "in", "both", "place", "and", "edmond", "and", "the", "jacobsen", "case", "be", "also", "significant", "because", "the", "court", "say", "that", "the", "reason", "this", "be", "not", "a", "search", "there", "use", "the", "dog", "sniff", "by", "analogy", "be", "because", "it", "compromise", "no", "legitimate", "privacy", "interest"]]}, {"text": "The language of the Court in Place is significant because it says that we are aware of no other investigative procedure that is so limited in both the manner in which the information is obtained and in the content of the information revealed.", "start": 1328.943, "stop": 1343.433, "duration": 14.49, "cleanText": [["the", "language", "of", "the", "court", "in", "place", "be", "significant", "because", "it", "say", "that", "we", "be", "aware", "of", "no", "other", "investigative", "procedure", "that", "be", "so", "limited", "in", "both", "the", "manner", "in", "which", "the", "information", "be", "obtain", "and", "in", "the", "content", "of", "the", "information", "reveal"]]}, {"text": "That language goes not only to why it's not a Fourth Amendment search but why the use of the dog sniff during a probable cause traffic stop here, where it doesn't prolong the duration, does not transform an otherwise lawful seizure into an unlawful one.", "start": 1343.433, "stop": 1359.697, "duration": 16.26, "cleanText": [["that", "language", "go", "not", "only", "to", "why", "it", "be", "not", "a", "fourth", "amendment", "search", "but", "why", "the", "use", "of", "the", "dog", "sniff", "during", "a", "probable", "because", "traffic", "stop", "here", "where", "it", "do", "not", "prolong", "the", "duration", "do", "not", "transform", "an", "otherwise", "lawful", "seizure", "into", "an", "unlawful", "one"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "David H. Souter", "textObjs": [{"text": "All right.", "start": 1359.697, "stop": 1360.113, "duration": 0.42, "cleanText": [["all", "right"]]}, {"text": "Do you... do you think it's... it's reasonable to say that if the police take dogs simply onto private property to sniff the foundations of houses, if they take dogs to the front door and ring the bell so that they hope the door will open, that there is... there is no compromise of a privacy interest?", "start": 1360.113, "stop": 1378.151, "duration": 18.04, "cleanText": [["do", "you", "do", "you", "think", "it", "be", "it", "be", "reasonable", "to", "say", "that", "if", "the", "police", "take", "dog", "simply", "onto", "private", "property", "to", "sniff", "the", "foundation", "of", "house", "if", "they", "take", "dog", "to", "the", "front", "door", "and", "ring", "the", "bell", "so", "that", "they", "hope", "the", "door", "will", "open", "that", "there", "be", "there", "be", "no", "compromise", "of", "a", "privacy", "interest"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Christopher A. Wray", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, there would be a question as to whether the officer, the human officer, that is, could be on private property... I take it from your hypothetical, Justice Souter... in the first place.", "start": 1378.151, "stop": 1387.827, "duration": 9.68, "cleanText": [["well", "there", "would", "be", "a", "question", "as", "to", "whether", "the", "officer", "the", "human", "officer", "that", "be", "could", "be", "on", "private", "property", "i", "take", "it", "from", "your", "hypothetical", "justice", "souter", "in", "the", "first", "place"]]}, {"text": "But--", "start": 1387.827, "stop": 1388.47, "duration": 0.64, "cleanText": [["but"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "David H. Souter", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, I mean, the Fourth Amendment analysis after Katz doesn't... doesn't depend on trespass, and... and you have said up to this point that there is no search.", "start": 1388.47, "stop": 1397.675, "duration": 9.2, "cleanText": [["well", "i", "mean", "the", "fourth", "amendment", "analysis", "after", "katz", "do", "not", "do", "not", "depend", "on", "trespass", "and", "and", "you", "have", "say", "up", "to", "this", "point", "that", "there", "be", "no", "search"]]}, {"text": "And then you have quite rightly said that we have had as a consideration in our minds analytically whether it's fair to say that what the police were doing involved any compromise of a privacy interest.", "start": 1397.675, "stop": 1411.217, "duration": 13.54, "cleanText": [["and", "then", "you", "have", "quite", "rightly", "say", "that", "we", "have", "have", "as", "a", "consideration", "in", "our", "mind", "analytically", "whether", "it", "be", "fair", "to", "say", "that", "what", "the", "police", "we", "be", "do", "involve", "any", "compromise", "of", "a", "privacy", "interest"]]}, {"text": "So I'm assuming... I'm assuming that the police can at least get to the foundation with a dog and they can certainly walk up to the front door and ring the bell.", "start": 1411.217, "stop": 1420.133, "duration": 8.92, "cleanText": [["so", "I", "be", "assume"], ["I", "be", "assume", "that", "the", "police", "can", "at", "least", "get", "to", "the", "foundation", "with", "a", "dog", "and", "they", "can", "certainly", "walk", "up", "to", "the", "front", "door", "and", "ring", "the", "bell"]]}, {"text": "And if they do that with a dog, for the purpose of letting the dog sniff and alert, if there's anything to alert to, is it fair to say that there is no compromise of the privacy interests of the people who own the house?", "start": 1420.133, "stop": 1431.362, "duration": 11.23, "cleanText": [["and", "if", "they", "do", "that", "with", "a", "dog", "for", "the", "purpose", "of", "let", "the", "dog", "sniff", "and", "alert", "if", "there", "be", "anything", "to", "alert", "to", "be", "it", "fair", "to", "say", "that", "there", "be", "no", "compromise", "of", "the", "privacy", "interest", "of", "the", "people", "who", "own", "the", "house"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Christopher A. Wray", "textObjs": [{"text": "--Our position would be... the answer to that question is yes.", "start": 1431.362, "stop": 1435.281, "duration": 3.92, "cleanText": [["our", "position", "would", "be", "the", "answer", "to", "that", "question", "be", "yes"]]}, {"text": "The Court does not have to resolve that issue to decide this case.", "start": 1435.281, "stop": 1438.809, "duration": 3.53, "cleanText": [["the", "court", "do", "not", "have", "to", "resolve", "that", "issue", "to", "decide", "this", "case"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Antonin Scalia", "textObjs": [{"text": "Of course, we could separate the home from the... from what happened here and still validate the search here if we held that it was a search, but was a reasonable one since all you find is that the person was carrying contraband.", "start": 1438.809, "stop": 1455.799, "duration": 16.99, "cleanText": [["of", "course", "we", "could", "separate", "the", "home", "from", "the", "from", "what", "happen", "here", "and", "still", "validate", "the", "search", "here", "if", "we", "hold", "that", "it", "be", "a", "search", "but", "be", "a", "reasonable", "one", "since", "all", "you", "find", "be", "that", "the", "person", "be", "carry", "contraband"]]}, {"text": "It's the only thing that's disclosed.", "start": 1455.799, "stop": 1457.49, "duration": 1.69, "cleanText": [["it", "be", "the", "only", "thing", "that", "be", "disclose"]]}, {"text": "Whereas, if you... if you did the same thing with... with regard to a house, which is a more sacrosanct part of one's privacy, it might be an unreasonable search.", "start": 1457.49, "stop": 1467.233, "duration": 9.74, "cleanText": [["whereas", "if", "you", "if", "you", "do", "the", "same", "thing", "with", "with", "regard", "to", "a", "house", "which", "be", "a", "more", "sacrosanct", "part", "of", "one", "s", "privacy", "it", "might", "be", "an", "unreasonable", "search"]]}, {"text": "We... we could reach that result if we wanted to, couldn't we?", "start": 1467.233, "stop": 1469.75, "duration": 2.52, "cleanText": [["we", "we", "could", "reach", "that", "result", "if", "we", "want", "to", "could", "not", "we"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Christopher A. Wray", "textObjs": [{"text": "I think you could, Justice Scalia.", "start": 1469.75, "stop": 1471.858, "duration": 2.11, "cleanText": [["i", "think", "you", "could", "justice", "scalia"]]}, {"text": "It's important to distinguish--", "start": 1471.858, "stop": 1473.094, "duration": 1.24, "cleanText": [["it", "be", "important", "to", "distinguish"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Sandra Day O'Connor", "textObjs": [{"text": "On the other hand, if it were a drug-selling neighborhood or around a park where drugs are frequently sold, would it be legitimate in your view for the police to take drug-sniffing dogs and walk around the public street where cars are parked around that known drug-selling area and see if they could sniff out some contraband in the cars?", "start": 1473.094, "stop": 1498.319, "duration": 25.22, "cleanText": [["on", "the", "other", "hand", "if", "it", "we", "be", "a", "drug", "selling", "neighborhood", "or", "around", "a", "park", "where", "drug", "be", "frequently", "sell", "would", "it", "be", "legitimate", "in", "your", "view", "for", "the", "police", "to", "take", "drug", "sniff", "dog", "and", "walk", "around", "the", "public", "street", "where", "car", "be", "park", "around", "that", "known", "drug", "sell", "area", "and", "see", "if", "they", "could", "sniff", "out", "some", "contraband", "in", "the", "car"]]}, {"text": "Is that okay?", "start": 1498.319, "stop": 1498.979, "duration": 0.66, "cleanText": [["be", "that", "okay"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Christopher A. Wray", "textObjs": [{"text": "--We believe it would be okay, Justice O'Connor.", "start": 1498.979, "stop": 1501.329, "duration": 2.35, "cleanText": [["we", "believe", "it", "would", "be", "okay", "justice", "oconnor"]]}, {"text": "It would be important not to use the dogs in a way to constitute a new seizure because in that case, you're not talking--", "start": 1501.329, "stop": 1508.471, "duration": 7.14, "cleanText": [["it", "would", "be", "important", "not", "to", "use", "the", "dog", "in", "a", "way", "to", "constitute", "a", "new", "seizure", "because", "in", "that", "case", "you", "be", "not", "talk"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Sandra Day O'Connor", "textObjs": [{"text": "I'm... I'm assuming parked cars.", "start": 1508.471, "stop": 1510.207, "duration": 1.74, "cleanText": [["I", "be"], ["I", "be", "assume", "parked", "car"]]}, {"text": "You haven't interrupted anybody.", "start": 1510.207, "stop": 1512.269, "duration": 2.06, "cleanText": [["you", "have", "not", "interrupt", "anybody"]]}, {"text": "Nobody is in the car, parked on a public street.", "start": 1512.269, "stop": 1515.037, "duration": 2.77, "cleanText": [["nobody", "be", "in", "the", "car", "park", "on", "a", "public", "street"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Christopher A. Wray", "textObjs": [{"text": "--In that instance, we believe that would be acceptable under the Fourth Amendment.", "start": 1515.037, "stop": 1520.155, "duration": 5.12, "cleanText": [["in", "that", "instance", "we", "believe", "that", "would", "be", "acceptable", "under", "the", "fourth", "amendment"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Anthony M. Kennedy", "textObjs": [{"text": "So you... you give no significance to the fact that this dog sniff was in the course of a lawful stop where the citizen's rights had already been curtailed to a significant extent?", "start": 1520.155, "stop": 1532.165, "duration": 12.01, "cleanText": [["so", "you", "you", "give", "no", "significance", "to", "the", "fact", "that", "this", "dog", "sniff", "be", "in", "the", "course", "of", "a", "lawful", "stop", "where", "the", "citizen", "s", "right", "have", "already", "be", "curtail", "to", "a", "significant", "extent"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Christopher A. Wray", "textObjs": [{"text": "We believe, Justice Kennedy, that the... that that context here makes this an even easier case under the Fourth Amendment, that is, the dog sniff not being a search compromising no legitimate privacy interests during the course of a lawful probable cause stop, which we know from Atwater... the officer could have simply placed the woman under full custodial arrest and taken her down to jail... was not an activity that transformed the seizure into an unlawful one.", "start": 1532.165, "stop": 1560.195, "duration": 28.03, "cleanText": [["we", "believe", "justice", "kennedy", "that", "the", "that", "that", "context", "here", "make", "this", "an", "even", "easy", "case", "under", "the", "fourth", "amendment", "that", "be", "the", "dog", "sniff", "not", "be", "a", "search", "compromise", "no", "legitimate", "privacy", "interest", "during", "the", "course", "of", "a", "lawful", "probable", "because", "stop", "which", "we", "know", "from", "atwater", "the", "officer", "could", "have", "simply", "place", "the", "woman", "under", "full", "custodial", "arrest", "and", "take", "her", "down", "to", "jail", "be", "not", "an", "activity", "that", "transform", "the", "seizure", "into", "an", "unlawful", "one"]]}, {"text": "The Illinois Supreme Court's concern and where we think they got off track was that they were concerned that the use of the dog sniff during this 9-minute traffic stop was that it transformed it... it used the language that it transformed the sniff into a drug investigation.", "start": 1560.195, "stop": 1576.376, "duration": 16.18, "cleanText": [["the", "illinois", "supreme", "court", "s", "concern", "and", "where", "we", "think", "they", "get", "off", "track", "be", "that", "they", "we", "be", "concern", "that", "the", "use", "of", "the", "dog", "sniff", "during", "this", "minute", "traffic", "stop", "be", "that", "it", "transform", "it", "it", "use", "the", "language", "that", "it", "transform", "the", "sniff", "into", "a", "drug", "investigation"]]}, {"text": "We would submit that the Fourth Amendment is about the reasonableness of searches and seizures and not about what the scope of the government's investigation is.", "start": 1576.376, "stop": 1584.261, "duration": 7.88, "cleanText": [["we", "would", "submit", "that", "the", "fourth", "amendment", "be", "about", "the", "reasonableness", "of", "search", "and", "seizure", "and", "not", "about", "what", "the", "scope", "of", "the", "government", "s", "investigation", "be"]]}, {"text": "And in that sense, the court got off track.", "start": 1584.261, "stop": 1587.233, "duration": 2.97, "cleanText": [["and", "in", "that", "sense", "the", "court", "get", "off", "track"]]}, {"text": "These... this is a... this is a means that law enforcement has been using properly in reliance on this Court's decision in Place, reinforced just 4 years ago in Edmond, for more than 21 years to detect everything from drugs to bombs to smuggled... we have beagles in the airports that smuggle produce that's being smuggled in.", "start": 1587.233, "stop": 1608.864, "duration": 21.63, "cleanText": [["these", "this", "be", "a", "this", "be", "a", "mean", "that", "law", "enforcement", "have", "be", "use", "properly", "in", "reliance", "on", "this", "court", "s", "decision", "in", "place", "reinforce", "just", "year", "ago", "in", "edmond", "for", "more", "than", "year", "to", "detect", "everything", "from", "drug", "to", "bomb", "to", "smuggle", "we", "have", "beagle", "in", "the", "airport", "that", "smuggle", "produce", "that", "be", "be", "smuggle", "in"]]}, {"text": "Dogs are used all over the country with great effectiveness in law enforcement, and the... we... that is a... a technique that we want to encourage law enforcement to pursue.", "start": 1608.864, "stop": 1620.215, "duration": 11.35, "cleanText": [["dog", "be", "use", "all", "over", "the", "country", "with", "great", "effectiveness", "in", "law", "enforcement", "and", "the", "we", "that", "be", "a", "a", "technique", "that", "we", "want", "to", "encourage", "law", "enforcement", "to", "pursue"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Ruth Bader Ginsburg", "textObjs": [{"text": "Are there... are there any manuals for law enforcement officers with respect to the time and place of using dogs, or it's just open season?", "start": 1620.215, "stop": 1633.097, "duration": 12.88, "cleanText": [["be", "there", "be", "there", "any", "manual", "for", "law", "enforcement", "officer", "with", "respect", "to", "the", "time", "and", "place", "of", "use", "dog", "or", "it", "be", "just", "open", "season"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Christopher A. Wray", "textObjs": [{"text": "Justice Ginsburg, there is extensive training of law enforcement to use dogs.", "start": 1633.097, "stop": 1638.791, "duration": 5.69, "cleanText": [["justice", "ginsburg", "there", "be", "extensive", "training", "of", "law", "enforcement", "to", "use", "dog"]]}, {"text": "It's a multi-week program that requires--", "start": 1638.791, "stop": 1641.27, "duration": 2.48, "cleanText": [["it", "be", "a", "multi", "week", "program", "that", "require"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Ruth Bader Ginsburg", "textObjs": [{"text": "I don't mean the training to make the dog alert properly.", "start": 1641.27, "stop": 1644.614, "duration": 3.34, "cleanText": [["i", "do", "not", "mean", "the", "training", "to", "make", "the", "dog", "alert", "properly"]]}, {"text": "How the police will use them, when, under what circumstances.", "start": 1644.614, "stop": 1649.609, "duration": 4.99, "cleanText": [["how", "the", "police", "will", "use", "them", "when", "under", "what", "circumstance"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Christopher A. Wray", "textObjs": [{"text": "--Justice Ginsburg, each agency has different policies about when they use dogs and what purpose they're trained for.", "start": 1649.609, "stop": 1656.957, "duration": 7.35, "cleanText": [["justice", "ginsburg", "each", "agency", "have", "different", "policy", "about", "when", "they", "use", "dog", "and", "what", "purpose", "they", "be", "train", "for"]]}, {"text": "In this case, as you heard, they're being used in the context of highway interdiction, and so they're trained to sniff around vehicles specifically.", "start": 1656.957, "stop": 1664.637, "duration": 7.68, "cleanText": [["in", "this", "case", "as", "you", "hear", "they", "be", "be", "use", "in", "the", "context", "of", "highway", "interdiction", "and", "so", "they", "be", "train", "to", "sniff", "around", "vehicle", "specifically"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "John Paul Stevens", "textObjs": [{"text": "--Thank you, Mr. Wray.", "start": 1664.637, "stop": 1666.761, "duration": 2.12, "cleanText": [["thank", "you", "mr", "wray"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Christopher A. Wray", "textObjs": [{"text": "Thank you.", "start": 1666.761, "stop": 1667.321, "duration": 0.56, "cleanText": [["thank", "you"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "John Paul Stevens", "textObjs": [{"text": "Mr. Meczyk.", "start": 1667.321, "stop": 1672.893, "duration": 5.57, "cleanText": [["mr", "meczyk"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Ralph E. Meczyk", "textObjs": [{"text": "Justice Stevens, and may it please the Court:", "start": 1672.893, "stop": 1675.661, "duration": 2.77, "cleanText": [["justice", "stevens", "and", "may", "it", "please", "the", "court"]]}, {"text": "The State does not offer any Fourth Amendment justification whatsoever in regards to... in this case.", "start": 1675.661, "stop": 1682.924, "duration": 7.26, "cleanText": [["the", "state", "do", "not", "offer", "any", "fourth", "amendment", "justification", "whatsoever", "in", "regard", "to", "in", "this", "case"]]}, {"text": "It argues instead that there... there was no need for any justification, and that is incorrect for two reasons.", "start": 1682.924, "stop": 1690.066, "duration": 7.14, "cleanText": [["it", "argue", "instead", "that", "there", "there", "be", "no", "need", "for", "any", "justification", "and", "that", "be", "incorrect", "for", "two", "reason"]]}, {"text": "The dog sniff in this case invaded a Fourth Amendment interest of Mr. Caballes in the context of a routine traffic search.", "start": 1690.066, "stop": 1700.84, "duration": 10.77, "cleanText": [["the", "dog", "sniff", "in", "this", "case", "invade", "a", "fourth", "amendment", "interest", "of", "mr", "caballes", "in", "the", "context", "of", "a", "routine", "traffic", "search"]]}, {"text": "The sniff in this case was, in fact, a search.", "start": 1700.84, "stop": 1704.184, "duration": 3.34, "cleanText": [["the", "sniff", "in", "this", "case", "be", "in", "fact", "a", "search"]]}, {"text": "Albeit it was a limited intrusion, it was still a search nonetheless.", "start": 1704.184, "stop": 1710.788, "duration": 6.6, "cleanText": [["albeit", "it", "be", "a", "limited", "intrusion", "it", "be", "still", "a", "search", "nonetheless"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Antonin Scalia", "textObjs": [{"text": "Why... why do you say that?", "start": 1710.788, "stop": 1712.357, "duration": 1.57, "cleanText": [["why", "why", "do", "you", "say", "that"]]}, {"text": "I mean, is... is anything that I observe a search?", "start": 1712.357, "stop": 1719.622, "duration": 7.27, "cleanText": [["i", "mean", "be", "be", "anything", "that", "i", "observe", "a", "search"]]}, {"text": "I mean, suppose I... I'm a policeman and... and I'm looking out for, I don't know, people with a nervous tic because I think that that might be somebody who's about to commit a crime or has committed a crime.", "start": 1719.622, "stop": 1731.76, "duration": 12.14, "cleanText": [["i", "mean", "suppose", "i"], ["I", "be", "a", "policeman", "and", "and", "I", "be", "look", "out", "for", "i", "do", "not", "know", "people", "with", "a", "nervous", "tic", "because", "i", "think", "that", "that", "might", "be", "somebody", "who", "be", "about", "to", "commit", "a", "crime", "or", "have", "commit", "a", "crime"]]}, {"text": "Have I searched that person because I... I observe something external?", "start": 1731.76, "stop": 1737.621, "duration": 5.86, "cleanText": [["have", "i", "search", "that", "person", "because", "i", "i", "observe", "something", "external"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Ralph E. Meczyk", "textObjs": [{"text": "Any observation I think--", "start": 1737.621, "stop": 1741.519, "duration": 3.9, "cleanText": [["any", "observation", "i", "think"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Antonin Scalia", "textObjs": [{"text": "Is there no difference between an investigation and a search?", "start": 1741.519, "stop": 1744.187, "duration": 2.67, "cleanText": [["be", "there", "no", "difference", "between", "an", "investigation", "and", "a", "search"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Ralph E. Meczyk", "textObjs": [{"text": "--There is in this case... see if I understand you correctly.", "start": 1744.187, "stop": 1749.881, "duration": 5.69, "cleanText": [["there", "be", "in", "this", "case", "see", "if", "i", "understand", "you", "correctly"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Antonin Scalia", "textObjs": [{"text": "No.", "start": 1749.881, "stop": 1751.079, "duration": 1.2, "cleanText": [["no"]]}, {"text": "It seems to me your brief and... and your statement here both seem to assume that there's a search whenever the police investigate.", "start": 1751.079, "stop": 1758.221, "duration": 7.14, "cleanText": [["it", "seem", "to", "me", "your", "brief", "and", "and", "your", "statement", "here", "both", "seem", "to", "assume", "that", "there", "be", "a", "search", "whenever", "the", "police", "investigate"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Ralph E. Meczyk", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well--", "start": 1758.221, "stop": 1758.964, "duration": 0.74, "cleanText": [["well"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Antonin Scalia", "textObjs": [{"text": "But that's not so.", "start": 1758.964, "stop": 1759.874, "duration": 0.91, "cleanText": [["but", "that", "be", "not", "so"]]}, {"text": "They... one can investigate without searching.", "start": 1759.874, "stop": 1762.307, "duration": 2.43, "cleanText": [["they", "one", "can", "investigate", "without", "search"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Ralph E. Meczyk", "textObjs": [{"text": "--Well, to... see if I understand your question correctly.", "start": 1762.307, "stop": 1764.62, "duration": 2.31, "cleanText": [["well", "to", "see", "if", "i", "understand", "your", "question", "correctly"]]}, {"text": "If you're looking with someone with that nervous tic, that would be something in open view or plain view.", "start": 1764.62, "stop": 1770.026, "duration": 5.41, "cleanText": [["if", "you", "be", "look", "with", "someone", "with", "that", "nervous", "tic", "that", "would", "be", "something", "in", "open", "view", "or", "plain", "view"]]}, {"text": "That's not the type of investigation I'm talking about.", "start": 1770.026, "stop": 1772.894, "duration": 2.87, "cleanText": [["that", "be", "not", "the", "type", "of", "investigation", "I", "be", "talk", "about"]]}, {"text": "There is in fact, most respectfully, an investigation technique here.", "start": 1772.894, "stop": 1777.002, "duration": 4.11, "cleanText": [["there", "be", "in", "fact", "most", "respectfully", "an", "investigation", "technique", "here"]]}, {"text": "There's an investigation measure.", "start": 1777.002, "stop": 1778.821, "duration": 1.82, "cleanText": [["there", "be", "an", "investigation", "measure"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Stephen G. Breyer", "textObjs": [{"text": "Yes, but that isn't the--", "start": 1778.821, "stop": 1779.276, "duration": 0.46, "cleanText": [["yes", "but", "that", "be", "not", "the"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Anthony M. Kennedy", "textObjs": [{"text": "What about a policeman who smells marijuana coming out of a car or a residence.", "start": 1779.276, "stop": 1783.074, "duration": 3.8, "cleanText": [["what", "about", "a", "policeman", "who", "smell", "marijuana", "come", "out", "of", "a", "car", "or", "a", "residence"]]}, {"text": "He's walking down the street, public street, and he smells marijuana.", "start": 1783.074, "stop": 1785.841, "duration": 2.77, "cleanText": [["he", "be", "walk", "down", "the", "street", "public", "street", "and", "he", "smell", "marijuana"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Ralph E. Meczyk", "textObjs": [{"text": "The only way I can analogize that, Justice Kennedy, is that it... that is akin to a plain smell or plain view.", "start": 1785.841, "stop": 1792.983, "duration": 7.14, "cleanText": [["the", "only", "way", "i", "can", "analogize", "that", "justice", "kennedy", "be", "that", "it", "that", "be", "akin", "to", "a", "plain", "smell", "or", "plain", "view"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Stephen G. Breyer", "textObjs": [{"text": "--All right.", "start": 1792.983, "stop": 1793.477, "duration": 0.49, "cleanText": [["all", "right"]]}, {"text": "So once you say that, you realize that there are billions and billions of searches that go on every day that the police don't have to justify at all.", "start": 1793.477, "stop": 1801.073, "duration": 7.6, "cleanText": [["so", "once", "you", "say", "that", "you", "realize", "that", "there", "be", "billion", "and", "billion", "of", "search", "that", "go", "on", "every", "day", "that", "the", "police", "do", "not", "have", "to", "justify", "at", "all"]]}, {"text": "They just look around.", "start": 1801.073, "stop": 1802.493, "duration": 1.42, "cleanText": [["they", "just", "look", "around"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Ralph E. Meczyk", "textObjs": [{"text": "I don't--", "start": 1802.493, "stop": 1803.402, "duration": 0.91, "cleanText": [["i", "do", "not"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Stephen G. Breyer", "textObjs": [{"text": "Okay?", "start": 1803.402, "stop": 1803.735, "duration": 0.33, "cleanText": [["okay"]]}, {"text": "There are billions of them.", "start": 1803.735, "stop": 1804.888, "duration": 1.15, "cleanText": [["there", "be", "billion", "of", "them"]]}, {"text": "So the real question is do they have to give a justification for this.", "start": 1804.888, "stop": 1807.943, "duration": 3.06, "cleanText": [["so", "the", "real", "question", "be", "do", "they", "have", "to", "give", "a", "justification", "for", "this"]]}, {"text": "And the argument that they don't is simply that it's not in the person's house.", "start": 1807.943, "stop": 1813.023, "duration": 5.08, "cleanText": [["and", "the", "argument", "that", "they", "do", "not", "be", "simply", "that", "it", "be", "not", "in", "the", "person", "s", "house"]]}, {"text": "When you go out in a public place, even in your car, you might run into people or animals with sharp noses.", "start": 1813.023, "stop": 1819.627, "duration": 6.6, "cleanText": [["when", "you", "go", "out", "in", "a", "public", "place", "even", "in", "your", "car", "you", "might", "run", "into", "people", "or", "animal", "with", "sharp", "nose"]]}, {"text": "And a lot of them can detect marijuana.", "start": 1819.627, "stop": 1822.599, "duration": 2.97, "cleanText": [["and", "a", "lot", "of", "them", "can", "detect", "marijuana"]]}, {"text": "And you know, maybe it's a Limburger cheese.", "start": 1822.599, "stop": 1825.283, "duration": 2.68, "cleanText": [["and", "you", "know", "maybe", "it", "be", "a", "limburger", "cheese"]]}, {"text": "I don't know.", "start": 1825.283, "stop": 1826.065, "duration": 0.78, "cleanText": [["i", "do", "not", "know"]]}, {"text": "[Laughter]", "start": 1826.065, "stop": 1826.974, "duration": 0.91, "cleanText": [["laughter"]]}, {"text": "But people are sniffing things that they don't sniff through windows into your house, but they do get odors in your car on the street.", "start": 1826.974, "stop": 1833.29, "duration": 6.32, "cleanText": [["but", "people", "be", "sniff", "thing", "that", "they", "do", "not", "sniff", "through", "window", "into", "your", "house", "but", "they", "do", "get", "odor", "in", "your", "car", "on", "the", "street"]]}, {"text": "So this is the kind of search.", "start": 1833.29, "stop": 1835.436, "duration": 2.15, "cleanText": [["so", "this", "be", "the", "kind", "of", "search"]]}, {"text": "Yes, it's a search, but one that the police don't have to justify.", "start": 1835.436, "stop": 1839.977, "duration": 4.54, "cleanText": [["yes", "it", "be", "a", "search", "but", "one", "that", "the", "police", "do", "not", "have", "to", "justify"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Ralph E. Meczyk", "textObjs": [{"text": "--But this is with a specific investigative tool.", "start": 1839.977, "stop": 1843.321, "duration": 3.34, "cleanText": [["but", "this", "be", "with", "a", "specific", "investigative", "tool"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Stephen G. Breyer", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, it's a specific investigative tool when I put on my glasses to look through a window.", "start": 1843.321, "stop": 1848.688, "duration": 5.37, "cleanText": [["well", "it", "be", "a", "specific", "investigative", "tool", "when", "i", "put", "on", "my", "glass", "to", "look", "through", "a", "window"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Ralph E. Meczyk", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, this is--", "start": 1848.688, "stop": 1849.431, "duration": 0.74, "cleanText": [["well", "this", "be"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Stephen G. Breyer", "textObjs": [{"text": "I don't see why it has to... why that matters if in fact all... if you go into a car, a police car, and you have... drive through the neighborhood and look around, you are using a specific investigative tool, the police car, to look around and find out what's going on.", "start": 1849.431, "stop": 1869.427, "duration": 20, "cleanText": [["i", "do", "not", "see", "why", "it", "have", "to", "why", "that", "matter", "if", "in", "fact", "all", "if", "you", "go", "into", "a", "car", "a", "police", "car", "and", "you", "have", "drive", "through", "the", "neighborhood", "and", "look", "around", "you", "be", "use", "a", "specific", "investigative", "tool", "the", "police", "car", "to", "look", "around", "and", "find", "out", "what", "be", "go", "on"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Ralph E. Meczyk", "textObjs": [{"text": "--This is a far more... most respectfully, this is a far more sophisticated investigative tool.", "start": 1869.427, "stop": 1875.522, "duration": 6.1, "cleanText": [["this", "be", "a", "far", "more", "most", "respectfully", "this", "be", "a", "far", "more", "sophisticated", "investigative", "tool"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Stephen G. Breyer", "textObjs": [{"text": "What I'm trying to get to is in my own mind it's not a question of the tools.", "start": 1875.522, "stop": 1878.744, "duration": 3.22, "cleanText": [["what", "I", "be", "try", "to", "get", "to", "be", "in", "my", "own", "mind", "it", "be", "not", "a", "question", "of", "the", "tool"]]}, {"text": "It's a question of the expectation of privacy.", "start": 1878.744, "stop": 1881.921, "duration": 3.18, "cleanText": [["it", "be", "a", "question", "of", "the", "expectation", "of", "privacy"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Ralph E. Meczyk", "textObjs": [{"text": "Then maybe I can see if I could answer your question.", "start": 1881.921, "stop": 1885.719, "duration": 3.8, "cleanText": [["then", "maybe", "i", "can", "see", "if", "i", "could", "answer", "your", "question"]]}, {"text": "Mr. Caballes in this case indeed had an expectation of privacy.", "start": 1885.719, "stop": 1890.011, "duration": 4.29, "cleanText": [["mr", "caballes", "in", "this", "case", "indeed", "have", "an", "expectation", "of", "privacy"]]}, {"text": "When he was asked by the police officer in this case if he can consent to the search, he said no.", "start": 1890.011, "stop": 1897.07, "duration": 7.06, "cleanText": [["when", "he", "be", "ask", "by", "the", "police", "officer", "in", "this", "case", "if", "he", "can", "consent", "to", "the", "search", "he", "say", "no"]]}, {"text": "He did not want that law enforcement officer looking in--", "start": 1897.07, "stop": 1900.497, "duration": 3.43, "cleanText": [["he", "do", "not", "want", "that", "law", "enforcement", "officer", "look", "in"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Anthony M. Kennedy", "textObjs": [{"text": "But that never--", "start": 1900.497, "stop": 1901.695, "duration": 1.2, "cleanText": [["but", "that", "never"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Sandra Day O'Connor", "textObjs": [{"text": "Yes, but both Place and Edmond, opinions from this Court, said sniffs are not searches.", "start": 1901.695, "stop": 1907.063, "duration": 5.37, "cleanText": [["yes", "but", "both", "place", "and", "edmond", "opinion", "from", "this", "court", "say", "sniff", "be", "not", "search"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Ralph E. Meczyk", "textObjs": [{"text": "--Well, I--", "start": 1907.063, "stop": 1907.639, "duration": 0.58, "cleanText": [["well", "i"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Sandra Day O'Connor", "textObjs": [{"text": "Do you want us to reverse that?", "start": 1907.639, "stop": 1908.837, "duration": 1.2, "cleanText": [["do", "you", "want", "us", "to", "reverse", "that"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Ralph E. Meczyk", "textObjs": [{"text": "--Justice O'Connor, I do not... I do not want you to reverse Place.", "start": 1908.837, "stop": 1913.378, "duration": 4.54, "cleanText": [["justice", "oconnor", "i", "do", "not", "i", "do", "not", "want", "you", "to", "reverse", "place"]]}, {"text": "Place, no pun intended--", "start": 1913.378, "stop": 1914.576, "duration": 1.2, "cleanText": [["place", "no", "pun", "intend"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Sandra Day O'Connor", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, and Edmond also said it's not a search.", "start": 1914.576, "stop": 1917.631, "duration": 3.06, "cleanText": [["well", "and", "edmond", "also", "say", "it", "be", "not", "a", "search"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Ralph E. Meczyk", "textObjs": [{"text": "--Well, there were--", "start": 1917.631, "stop": 1918.54, "duration": 0.91, "cleanText": [["well", "there", "we", "be"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Sandra Day O'Connor", "textObjs": [{"text": "It was the stop of the cars in that case that caused the result.", "start": 1918.54, "stop": 1923.248, "duration": 4.71, "cleanText": [["it", "be", "the", "stop", "of", "the", "car", "in", "that", "case", "that", "cause", "the", "result"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Ralph E. Meczyk", "textObjs": [{"text": "--The way I understand Place it was contextually limited.", "start": 1923.248, "stop": 1927.622, "duration": 4.37, "cleanText": [["the", "way", "i", "understand", "place", "it", "be", "contextually", "limited"]]}, {"text": "In Place, the whole purpose of the seizure, the taking of the luggage, was to submit it to a drug-detection sniff.", "start": 1927.622, "stop": 1935.22, "duration": 7.6, "cleanText": [["in", "place", "the", "whole", "purpose", "of", "the", "seizure", "the", "taking", "of", "the", "luggage", "be", "to", "submit", "it", "to", "a", "drug", "detection", "sniff"]]}, {"text": "That is the opinion authored by Your Honor, that specifically stated... I'm not going to say took for granted, but it specifically stated that the... the context... and that's what we have to look at Place... the--", "start": 1935.22, "stop": 1945.501, "duration": 10.28, "cleanText": [["that", "be", "the", "opinion", "author", "by", "your", "honor", "that", "specifically", "state"], ["I", "be", "not", "go", "to", "say", "take", "for", "grant", "but", "it", "specifically", "state", "that", "the", "the", "context", "and", "that", "be", "what", "we", "have", "to", "look", "at", "place", "the"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Sandra Day O'Connor", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, fine.", "start": 1945.501, "stop": 1945.806, "duration": 0.31, "cleanText": [["well", "fine"]]}, {"text": "We had a context there where we supported it, but in the process said the sniff, the dog sniff, was not a search.", "start": 1945.806, "stop": 1951.733, "duration": 5.93, "cleanText": [["we", "have", "a", "context", "there", "where", "we", "support", "it", "but", "in", "the", "process", "say", "the", "sniff", "the", "dog", "sniff", "be", "not", "a", "search"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Ralph E. Meczyk", "textObjs": [{"text": "--Well, I... I--", "start": 1951.733, "stop": 1952.659, "duration": 0.93, "cleanText": [["well", "i", "i"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Sandra Day O'Connor", "textObjs": [{"text": "So you want us to say something else here.", "start": 1952.659, "stop": 1954.705, "duration": 2.05, "cleanText": [["so", "you", "want", "us", "to", "say", "something", "else", "here"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Ralph E. Meczyk", "textObjs": [{"text": "--Well, I think that first in... in that case, in Place, the... the Court--", "start": 1954.705, "stop": 1958.67, "duration": 3.97, "cleanText": [["well", "i", "think", "that", "first", "in", "in", "that", "case", "in", "place", "the", "the", "court"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Sandra Day O'Connor", "textObjs": [{"text": "The context here was a legitimate traffic stop.", "start": 1958.67, "stop": 1961.187, "duration": 2.52, "cleanText": [["the", "context", "here", "be", "a", "legitimate", "traffic", "stop"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Ralph E. Meczyk", "textObjs": [{"text": "--But it was... unlike Place, the legitimate traffic stop here was completely unrelated to the purpose of the dog sniff.", "start": 1961.187, "stop": 1969.36, "duration": 8.17, "cleanText": [["but", "it", "be", "unlike", "place", "the", "legitimate", "traffic", "stop", "here", "be", "completely", "unrelated", "to", "the", "purpose", "of", "the", "dog", "sniff"]]}, {"text": "There was an absolute--", "start": 1969.36, "stop": 1970.846, "duration": 1.49, "cleanText": [["there", "be", "an", "absolute"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Sandra Day O'Connor", "textObjs": [{"text": "The dog sniff is not a search.", "start": 1970.846, "stop": 1972.583, "duration": 1.74, "cleanText": [["the", "dog", "sniff", "be", "not", "a", "search"]]}, {"text": "What difference does it make?", "start": 1972.583, "stop": 1973.985, "duration": 1.4, "cleanText": [["what", "difference", "do", "it", "make"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Ralph E. Meczyk", "textObjs": [{"text": "--Well, again, I would again respectfully assert that the dog sniff is a search and the way Place was decided, first, the decision had to be made, in the context of... of that case, what was worse.", "start": 1973.985, "stop": 1985.79, "duration": 11.81, "cleanText": [["well", "again", "i", "would", "again", "respectfully", "assert", "that", "the", "dog", "sniff", "be", "a", "search", "and", "the", "way", "place", "be", "decide", "first", "the", "decision", "have", "to", "be", "make", "in", "the", "context", "of", "of", "that", "case", "what", "be", "bad"]]}, {"text": "What were they going to do with the luggage?", "start": 1985.79, "stop": 1987.731, "duration": 1.94, "cleanText": [["what", "we", "be", "they", "go", "to", "do", "with", "the", "luggage"]]}, {"text": "Were they going to open the luggage first?", "start": 1987.731, "stop": 1989.505, "duration": 1.77, "cleanText": [["we", "be", "they", "go", "to", "open", "the", "luggage", "first"]]}, {"text": "So, of course, the Court had to decide in that case that it wasn't that kind of a... a search.", "start": 1989.505, "stop": 1996.443, "duration": 6.94, "cleanText": [["so", "of", "course", "the", "court", "have", "to", "decide", "in", "that", "case", "that", "it", "be", "not", "that", "kind", "of", "a", "a", "search"]]}, {"text": "It wasn't as egregious a search as actually opening the luggage.", "start": 1996.443, "stop": 1999.786, "duration": 3.34, "cleanText": [["it", "be", "not", "as", "egregious", "a", "search", "as", "actually", "open", "the", "luggage"]]}, {"text": "Then you--", "start": 1999.786, "stop": 2000.529, "duration": 0.74, "cleanText": [["then", "you"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Sandra Day O'Connor", "textObjs": [{"text": "This... the trunk of the car didn't have to be opened here.", "start": 2000.529, "stop": 2003.213, "duration": 2.68, "cleanText": [["this", "the", "trunk", "of", "the", "car", "do", "not", "have", "to", "be", "open", "here"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Ralph E. Meczyk", "textObjs": [{"text": "--I'm sorry, Your Honor.", "start": 2003.213, "stop": 2004.494, "duration": 1.28, "cleanText": [["I", "be", "sorry", "your", "honor"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Sandra Day O'Connor", "textObjs": [{"text": "The trunk of the vehicle did not have to be opened here.", "start": 2004.494, "stop": 2007.838, "duration": 3.34, "cleanText": [["the", "trunk", "of", "the", "vehicle", "do", "not", "have", "to", "be", "open", "here"]]}, {"text": "You're talking about a dog sniffing on the exterior of the vehicle that was legitimately stopped for a traffic violation.", "start": 2007.838, "stop": 2015.64, "duration": 7.8, "cleanText": [["you", "be", "talk", "about", "a", "dog", "sniff", "on", "the", "exterior", "of", "the", "vehicle", "that", "be", "legitimately", "stop", "for", "a", "traffic", "violation"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Ralph E. Meczyk", "textObjs": [{"text": "Again, in this context, unlike in Place, there was absolutely no relationship between the... the dog sniff and the dog sniff of Caballes' trunk and the sniff of the luggage that was placed at LaGuardia Airport in Place.", "start": 2015.64, "stop": 2029.302, "duration": 13.66, "cleanText": [["again", "in", "this", "context", "unlike", "in", "place", "there", "be", "absolutely", "no", "relationship", "between", "the", "the", "dog", "sniff", "and", "the", "dog", "sniff", "of", "caballes", "trunk", "and", "the", "sniff", "of", "the", "luggage", "that", "be", "place", "at", "laguardia", "airport", "in", "place"]]}, {"text": "There's a great distinction.", "start": 2029.302, "stop": 2030.417, "duration": 1.12, "cleanText": [["there", "be", "a", "great", "distinction"]]}, {"text": "Moreover--", "start": 2030.417, "stop": 2031.365, "duration": 0.95, "cleanText": [["moreover"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Antonin Scalia", "textObjs": [{"text": "Suppose a policeman follows me around.", "start": 2031.365, "stop": 2034.503, "duration": 3.14, "cleanText": [["suppose", "a", "policeman", "follow", "me", "around"]]}, {"text": "He just... just follows me around, observing with his... with plain eyes.", "start": 2034.503, "stop": 2040.819, "duration": 6.32, "cleanText": [["he", "just", "just", "follow", "me", "around", "observe", "with", "his", "with", "plain", "eye"]]}, {"text": "Now, is that a search?", "start": 2040.819, "stop": 2041.274, "duration": 0.45, "cleanText": [["now", "be", "that", "a", "search"]]}, {"text": "Does he need probable cause to do that?", "start": 2041.274, "stop": 2044.163, "duration": 2.89, "cleanText": [["do", "he", "need", "probable", "because", "to", "do", "that"]]}, {"text": "Now, he's wasting his time and he's wasting public money and maybe he should get fired for doing it, if he has no reason to follow me.", "start": 2044.163, "stop": 2051.222, "duration": 7.06, "cleanText": [["now", "he", "have", "waste", "his", "time", "and", "he", "be", "waste", "public", "money", "and", "maybe", "he", "should", "get", "fire", "for", "do", "it", "if", "he", "have", "no", "reason", "to", "follow", "me"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Ralph E. Meczyk", "textObjs": [{"text": "--It's not a search.", "start": 2051.222, "stop": 2052.13, "duration": 0.91, "cleanText": [["it", "be", "not", "a", "search"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Antonin Scalia", "textObjs": [{"text": "And maybe... maybe I'd have a harassment action against him if he does it, you know, blatantly.", "start": 2052.13, "stop": 2059.19, "duration": 7.06, "cleanText": [["and", "maybe", "maybe", "I", "would", "have", "a", "harassment", "action", "against", "him", "if", "he", "do", "it", "you", "know", "blatantly"]]}, {"text": "But is that a search?", "start": 2059.19, "stop": 2060.304, "duration": 1.11, "cleanText": [["but", "be", "that", "a", "search"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Ralph E. Meczyk", "textObjs": [{"text": "It is not a search.", "start": 2060.304, "stop": 2060.759, "duration": 0.45, "cleanText": [["it", "be", "not", "a", "search"]]}, {"text": "If he follows you--", "start": 2060.759, "stop": 2061.685, "duration": 0.93, "cleanText": [["if", "he", "follow", "you"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Antonin Scalia", "textObjs": [{"text": "Okay.", "start": 2061.685, "stop": 2062.161, "duration": 0.48, "cleanText": [["okay"]]}, {"text": "So... so the mere fact that one is in investigating something doesn't make it a search.", "start": 2062.161, "stop": 2066.498, "duration": 4.34, "cleanText": [["so", "so", "the", "mere", "fact", "that", "one", "be", "in", "investigate", "something", "do", "not", "make", "it", "a", "search"]]}, {"text": "What does make it a search?", "start": 2066.498, "stop": 2067.696, "duration": 1.2, "cleanText": [["what", "do", "make", "it", "a", "search"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Ralph E. Meczyk", "textObjs": [{"text": "--Well--", "start": 2067.696, "stop": 2068.438, "duration": 0.74, "cleanText": [["well"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Antonin Scalia", "textObjs": [{"text": "The fact that you find out something?", "start": 2068.438, "stop": 2070.175, "duration": 1.74, "cleanText": [["the", "fact", "that", "you", "find", "out", "something"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Ralph E. Meczyk", "textObjs": [{"text": "--I think here the most distinctive point here is that Caballes had already been stopped unlike the hypothetical that you just presented to me.", "start": 2070.175, "stop": 2077.355, "duration": 7.18, "cleanText": [["i", "think", "here", "the", "most", "distinctive", "point", "here", "be", "that", "caballes", "have", "already", "be", "stop", "unlike", "the", "hypothetical", "that", "you", "just", "present", "to", "me"]]}, {"text": "Caballes was already stopped for one... for probable cause.", "start": 2077.355, "stop": 2080.411, "duration": 3.06, "cleanText": [["caballes", "be", "already", "stop", "for", "one", "for", "probable", "because"]]}, {"text": "There's no question about that.", "start": 2080.411, "stop": 2081.525, "duration": 1.11, "cleanText": [["there", "be", "no", "question", "about", "that"]]}, {"text": "But then now the police launch into a wholly unrelated investigation that's--", "start": 2081.525, "stop": 2088.212, "duration": 6.69, "cleanText": [["but", "then", "now", "the", "police", "launch", "into", "a", "wholly", "unrelated", "investigation", "that", "be"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Antonin Scalia", "textObjs": [{"text": "You think it would be better if he hadn't been stopped?", "start": 2088.212, "stop": 2090.32, "duration": 2.11, "cleanText": [["you", "think", "it", "would", "be", "well", "if", "he", "have", "not", "be", "stop"]]}, {"text": "If... if they just... just randomly walked up to somebody who was going through a toll booth and had the dog sniff the car, you think that would be a better case--", "start": 2090.32, "stop": 2101.959, "duration": 11.64, "cleanText": [["if", "if", "they", "just", "just", "randomly", "walk", "up", "to", "somebody", "who", "be", "go", "through", "a", "toll", "booth", "and", "have", "the", "dog", "sniff", "the", "car", "you", "think", "that", "would", "be", "a", "good", "case"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Ralph E. Meczyk", "textObjs": [{"text": "--I think--", "start": 2101.959, "stop": 2103.323, "duration": 1.36, "cleanText": [["i", "think"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Antonin Scalia", "textObjs": [{"text": "--for allowing it than... than yours?", "start": 2103.323, "stop": 2104.742, "duration": 1.42, "cleanText": [["for", "allow", "it", "than", "than", "yours"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Ralph E. Meczyk", "textObjs": [{"text": "--Even in that case, even in a hypothetical where they used the dog for a toll booth, I have a problem with that.", "start": 2104.742, "stop": 2110.01, "duration": 5.27, "cleanText": [["even", "in", "that", "case", "even", "in", "a", "hypothetical", "where", "they", "use", "the", "dog", "for", "a", "toll", "booth", "i", "have", "a", "problem", "with", "that"]]}, {"text": "That to me is a search.", "start": 2110.01, "stop": 2111.141, "duration": 1.13, "cleanText": [["that", "to", "me", "be", "a", "search"]]}, {"text": "It's different than... I would assert it's different than if they walked... one of the hypotheticals that the Justices asked my adversary in this case, when they asked, well, what if they walked the dog instead around a... parked cars or parked cars at a stadium?", "start": 2111.141, "stop": 2125.159, "duration": 14.02, "cleanText": [["it", "be", "different", "than", "i", "would", "assert", "it", "be", "different", "than", "if", "they", "walk", "one", "of", "the", "hypothetical", "that", "the", "justice", "ask", "my", "adversary", "in", "this", "case", "when", "they", "ask", "well", "what", "if", "they", "walk", "the", "dog", "instead", "around", "a", "parked", "car", "or", "parked", "car", "at", "a", "stadium"]]}, {"text": "It depends for what purpose they want to walk those parked... that dog around those parked cars.", "start": 2125.159, "stop": 2130.194, "duration": 5.03, "cleanText": [["it", "depend", "for", "what", "purpose", "they", "want", "to", "walk", "those", "parked", "that", "dog", "around", "those", "parked", "car"]]}, {"text": "My assertion is--", "start": 2130.194, "stop": 2131.392, "duration": 1.2, "cleanText": [["my", "assertion", "be"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Ruth Bader Ginsburg", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, they said it's to find out if there's any contraband.", "start": 2131.392, "stop": 2134.614, "duration": 3.22, "cleanText": [["well", "they", "say", "it", "be", "to", "find", "out", "if", "there", "be", "any", "contraband"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Ralph E. Meczyk", "textObjs": [{"text": "--I'm sorry, Your Honor.", "start": 2134.614, "stop": 2135.85, "duration": 1.24, "cleanText": [["I", "be", "sorry", "your", "honor"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Ruth Bader Ginsburg", "textObjs": [{"text": "The answer was they are at liberty... the police are at liberty to use dogs to find contraband.", "start": 2135.85, "stop": 2146.874, "duration": 11.02, "cleanText": [["the", "answer", "be", "they", "be", "at", "liberty", "the", "police", "be", "at", "liberty", "to", "use", "dog", "to", "find", "contraband"]]}, {"text": "And your... Illinois I think was very candid with the Court in saying we have taken from your decisions that a dog sniff is not a search.", "start": 2146.874, "stop": 2158.141, "duration": 11.27, "cleanText": [["and", "your", "illinois", "i", "think", "be", "very", "candid", "with", "the", "court", "in", "say", "we", "have", "take", "from", "your", "decision", "that", "a", "dog", "sniff", "be", "not", "a", "search"]]}, {"text": "So anything else is a matter of police policy.", "start": 2158.141, "stop": 2161.856, "duration": 3.72, "cleanText": [["so", "anything", "else", "be", "a", "matter", "of", "police", "policy"]]}, {"text": "It had nothing to do with the Fourth Amendment.", "start": 2161.856, "stop": 2163.714, "duration": 1.86, "cleanText": [["it", "have", "nothing", "to", "do", "with", "the", "fourth", "amendment"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Ralph E. Meczyk", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, I... I strongly differ.", "start": 2163.714, "stop": 2166.853, "duration": 3.14, "cleanText": [["well", "i", "i", "strongly", "differ"]]}, {"text": "I have to look at the purpose that they are going to use the dog for.", "start": 2166.853, "stop": 2169.825, "duration": 2.97, "cleanText": [["i", "have", "to", "look", "at", "the", "purpose", "that", "they", "be", "go", "to", "use", "the", "dog", "for"]]}, {"text": "This Court--", "start": 2169.825, "stop": 2170.318, "duration": 0.49, "cleanText": [["this", "court"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Sandra Day O'Connor", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, does it matter if, for instance, in today's world on Capitol Hill we're concerned about terrorist attacks.", "start": 2170.318, "stop": 2177.377, "duration": 7.06, "cleanText": [["well", "do", "it", "matter", "if", "for", "instance", "in", "today", "s", "world", "on", "capitol", "hill", "we", "be", "concern", "about", "terrorist", "attack"]]}, {"text": "What if the dog is trained to alert to explosives?", "start": 2177.377, "stop": 2181.797, "duration": 4.42, "cleanText": [["what", "if", "the", "dog", "be", "train", "to", "alert", "to", "explosives"]]}, {"text": "Now, can the police just decide they're going to sniff any car that's parked on Capitol Hill?", "start": 2181.797, "stop": 2189.144, "duration": 7.35, "cleanText": [["now", "can", "the", "police", "just", "decide", "they", "be", "go", "to", "sniff", "any", "car", "that", "be", "park", "on", "capitol", "hill"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Ralph E. Meczyk", "textObjs": [{"text": "--Justice O'Connor, it depends on the purpose.", "start": 2189.144, "stop": 2191.085, "duration": 1.94, "cleanText": [["justice", "oconnor", "it", "depend", "on", "the", "purpose"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Sandra Day O'Connor", "textObjs": [{"text": "Yes or no, in your view.", "start": 2191.085, "stop": 2192.821, "duration": 1.74, "cleanText": [["yes", "or", "no", "in", "your", "view"]]}, {"text": "The purpose is to disclose potential explosives in a parked vehicle.", "start": 2192.821, "stop": 2198.698, "duration": 5.88, "cleanText": [["the", "purpose", "be", "to", "disclose", "potential", "explosive", "in", "a", "parked", "vehicle"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Ralph E. Meczyk", "textObjs": [{"text": "The answer is yes.", "start": 2198.698, "stop": 2199.918, "duration": 1.22, "cleanText": [["the", "answer", "be", "yes"]]}, {"text": "I have no problem whatsoever.", "start": 2199.918, "stop": 2201.404, "duration": 1.49, "cleanText": [["i", "have", "no", "problem", "whatsoever"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Sandra Day O'Connor", "textObjs": [{"text": "Wherever it is.", "start": 2201.404, "stop": 2202.109, "duration": 0.7, "cleanText": [["wherever", "it", "be"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Ralph E. Meczyk", "textObjs": [{"text": "Wherever it is because I look at it as a public safety exception.", "start": 2202.109, "stop": 2205.574, "duration": 3.47, "cleanText": [["wherever", "it", "be", "because", "i", "look", "at", "it", "as", "a", "public", "safety", "exception"]]}, {"text": "And this Court in the Edmond case specifically condemned a general search... a general crime... let me use the exact words.", "start": 2205.574, "stop": 2216.615, "duration": 11.04, "cleanText": [["and", "this", "court", "in", "the", "edmond", "case", "specifically", "condemn", "a", "general", "search", "a", "general", "crime", "let", "me", "use", "the", "exact", "word"]]}, {"text": "General interest in crime control, to quote the Edmond case.", "start": 2216.615, "stop": 2223.49, "duration": 6.88, "cleanText": [["general", "interest", "in", "crime", "control", "to", "quote", "the", "edmond", "case"]]}, {"text": "And that's--", "start": 2223.49, "stop": 2224.317, "duration": 0.83, "cleanText": [["and", "that", "be"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Stephen G. Breyer", "textObjs": [{"text": "I still want to go back to my question because I think you may have an answer to it and I want to focus you--", "start": 2224.317, "stop": 2229.025, "duration": 4.71, "cleanText": [["i", "still", "want", "to", "go", "back", "to", "my", "question", "because", "i", "think", "you", "may", "have", "an", "answer", "to", "it", "and", "i", "want", "to", "focus", "you"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Ralph E. Meczyk", "textObjs": [{"text": "--I'm struggling, yes.", "start": 2229.025, "stop": 2229.768, "duration": 0.74, "cleanText": [["I", "be", "struggle", "yes"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Stephen G. Breyer", "textObjs": [{"text": "--I want to focus you on the question.", "start": 2229.768, "stop": 2231.087, "duration": 1.32, "cleanText": [["i", "want", "to", "focus", "you", "on", "the", "question"]]}, {"text": "I think what you're doing, which is a reasonable thing to do, but it isn't my approach, look to the English definition of search.", "start": 2231.087, "stop": 2238.313, "duration": 7.23, "cleanText": [["i", "think", "what", "you", "be", "do", "which", "be", "a", "reasonable", "thing", "to", "do", "but", "it", "be", "not", "my", "approach", "look", "to", "the", "english", "definition", "of", "search"]]}, {"text": "I say forget that.", "start": 2238.313, "stop": 2240.004, "duration": 1.69, "cleanText": [["i", "say", "forget", "that"]]}, {"text": "Let's look to the Fourth Amendment because there are a whole range of searches that don't even fall within the Fourth Amendment in the sense that we don't need a justification.", "start": 2240.004, "stop": 2249.375, "duration": 9.37, "cleanText": [["let", "us", "look", "to", "the", "fourth", "amendment", "because", "there", "be", "a", "whole", "range", "of", "search", "that", "do", "not", "even", "fall", "within", "the", "fourth", "amendment", "in", "the", "sense", "that", "we", "do", "not", "need", "a", "justification"]]}, {"text": "And I take Place as saying that dog sniffs is one of those, whether it does or doesn't use the word English search.", "start": 2249.375, "stop": 2256.062, "duration": 6.69, "cleanText": [["and", "i", "take", "place", "as", "say", "that", "dog", "sniff", "be", "one", "of", "those", "whether", "it", "do", "or", "do", "not", "use", "the", "word", "english", "search"]]}, {"text": "So I want to know why it is that this dog search is one of the ones that's a Fourth Amendment search, i.e., one of the ones that requires a justification in terms of what the Fourth Amendment is about, privacy.", "start": 2256.062, "stop": 2272.78, "duration": 16.72, "cleanText": [["so", "i", "want", "to", "know", "why", "it", "be", "that", "this", "dog", "search", "be", "one", "of", "the", "one", "that", "be", "a", "fourth", "amendment", "search", "ie", "one", "of", "the", "one", "that", "require", "a", "justification", "in", "term", "of", "what", "the", "fourth", "amendment", "be", "about", "privacy"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Ralph E. Meczyk", "textObjs": [{"text": "It invades a public... I'm sorry.", "start": 2272.78, "stop": 2275.587, "duration": 2.81, "cleanText": [["it", "invade", "a", "public"], ["I", "be", "sorry"]]}, {"text": "It invades a private space that in this particular case the respondent Caballes had a privacy interest in, that he wanted to exclude the whole world from going inside his trunk.", "start": 2275.587, "stop": 2290.53, "duration": 14.94, "cleanText": [["it", "invade", "a", "private", "space", "that", "in", "this", "particular", "case", "the", "respondent", "caballes", "have", "a", "privacy", "interest", "in", "that", "he", "want", "to", "exclude", "the", "whole", "world", "from", "go", "inside", "his", "trunk"]]}, {"text": "That's the difference.", "start": 2290.53, "stop": 2292.016, "duration": 1.49, "cleanText": [["that", "be", "the", "difference"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "John Paul Stevens", "textObjs": [{"text": "Yes, but you don't respond to one point in Place, if I remember correctly.", "start": 2292.016, "stop": 2295.527, "duration": 3.51, "cleanText": [["yes", "but", "you", "do", "not", "respond", "to", "one", "point", "in", "place", "if", "i", "remember", "correctly"]]}, {"text": "It must be a legitimate expectation of privacy, and if the only thing the dog can detect is something illegitimate, how can you say there's an invasion of a legitimate expectation in privacy?", "start": 2295.527, "stop": 2307.044, "duration": 11.52, "cleanText": [["it", "must", "be", "a", "legitimate", "expectation", "of", "privacy", "and", "if", "the", "only", "thing", "the", "dog", "can", "detect", "be", "something", "illegitimate", "how", "can", "you", "say", "there", "be", "an", "invasion", "of", "a", "legitimate", "expectation", "in", "privacy"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Ralph E. Meczyk", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, it is... it's true that one does not have an expectation of privacy in contraband, but by the same token, I have an expectation or Mr. Caballes had an expectation of... of privacy of what's inside that closed trunk, his car.", "start": 2307.044, "stop": 2325.742, "duration": 18.7, "cleanText": [["well", "it", "be", "it", "be", "true", "that", "one", "do", "not", "have", "an", "expectation", "of", "privacy", "in", "contraband", "but", "by", "the", "same", "token", "i", "have", "an", "expectation", "or", "mr", "caballes", "have", "an", "expectation", "of", "of", "privacy", "of", "what", "be", "inside", "that", "close", "trunk", "his", "car"]]}, {"text": "The Carroll doctrine is still good law.", "start": 2325.742, "stop": 2328.054, "duration": 2.31, "cleanText": [["the", "carroll", "doctrine", "be", "still", "good", "law"]]}, {"text": "We still apply the Fourth Amendment in cars.", "start": 2328.054, "stop": 2331.026, "duration": 2.97, "cleanText": [["we", "still", "apply", "the", "fourth", "amendment", "in", "car"]]}, {"text": "It's true that the home is sacrosanct, but just because it's a home, it's not a talisman where... where the Fourth Amendment no longer applies.", "start": 2331.026, "stop": 2338.745, "duration": 7.72, "cleanText": [["it", "be", "true", "that", "the", "home", "be", "sacrosanct", "but", "just", "because", "it", "be", "a", "home", "it", "be", "not", "a", "talisman", "where", "where", "the", "fourth", "amendment", "no", "long", "applies"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Ruth Bader Ginsburg", "textObjs": [{"text": "There was something you said in... in your brief that I thought was unclear.", "start": 2338.745, "stop": 2343.453, "duration": 4.71, "cleanText": [["there", "be", "something", "you", "say", "in", "in", "your", "brief", "that", "i", "think", "be", "unclear"]]}, {"text": "So may I ask you--", "start": 2343.453, "stop": 2346.63, "duration": 3.18, "cleanText": [["so", "may", "i", "ask", "you"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Ralph E. Meczyk", "textObjs": [{"text": "Of course.", "start": 2346.63, "stop": 2347.373, "duration": 0.74, "cleanText": [["of", "course"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Ruth Bader Ginsburg", "textObjs": [{"text": "--if Officer Gillette, the one who did the arrest for speeding, had a dog in the back of his car, instead of having the second officer come with the dog, would it have been permissible?", "start": 2347.373, "stop": 2363.803, "duration": 16.43, "cleanText": [["if", "officer", "gillette", "the", "one", "who", "do", "the", "arrest", "for", "speeding", "have", "a", "dog", "in", "the", "back", "of", "his", "car", "instead", "of", "have", "the", "second", "officer", "come", "with", "the", "dog", "would", "it", "have", "be", "permissible"]]}, {"text": "I thought you had conceded that it would be a different situation if the dog was already there when the car stopped.", "start": 2363.803, "stop": 2370.036, "duration": 6.23, "cleanText": [["i", "think", "you", "have", "concede", "that", "it", "would", "be", "a", "different", "situation", "if", "the", "dog", "be", "already", "there", "when", "the", "car", "stop"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Ralph E. Meczyk", "textObjs": [{"text": "First of all, Justice Ginsburg, my recollection is that Trooper Gillette, who was the officer who stopped Caballes, did not have a... a dog in the car.", "start": 2370.036, "stop": 2382.296, "duration": 12.26, "cleanText": [["first", "of", "all", "justice", "ginsburg", "my", "recollection", "be", "that", "trooper", "gillette", "who", "be", "the", "officer", "who", "stop", "caballes", "do", "not", "have", "a", "a", "dog", "in", "the", "car"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Ruth Bader Ginsburg", "textObjs": [{"text": "No, he didn't, but I'm asking you to imagine that he did.", "start": 2382.296, "stop": 2385.722, "duration": 3.43, "cleanText": [["no", "he", "do", "not", "but", "I", "be", "ask", "you", "to", "imagine", "that", "he", "do"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Ralph E. Meczyk", "textObjs": [{"text": "I see.", "start": 2385.722, "stop": 2386.111, "duration": 0.39, "cleanText": [["i", "see"]]}, {"text": "If he had a dog in the car and the dog just happened to have alerted without his cuing the dog or walking the dog... and I'll answer that in a moment too... that would be pure serendipity.", "start": 2386.111, "stop": 2399.636, "duration": 13.53, "cleanText": [["if", "he", "have", "a", "dog", "in", "the", "car", "and", "the", "dog", "just", "happen", "to", "have", "alert", "without", "his", "cue", "the", "dog", "or", "walk", "the", "dog", "and", "I", "will", "answer", "that", "in", "a", "moment", "too", "that", "would", "be", "pure", "serendipity"]]}, {"text": "That might happen.", "start": 2399.636, "stop": 2400.417, "duration": 0.78, "cleanText": [["that", "might", "happen"]]}, {"text": "If... if the dog just happened to have alerted.", "start": 2400.417, "stop": 2403.389, "duration": 2.97, "cleanText": [["if", "if", "the", "dog", "just", "happen", "to", "have", "alert"]]}, {"text": "But if the troopers deliberately drove the car close by... and in reality, that's not what happens.", "start": 2403.389, "stop": 2410.902, "duration": 7.51, "cleanText": [["but", "if", "the", "trooper", "deliberately", "drive", "the", "car", "close", "by", "and", "in", "reality", "that", "be", "not", "what", "happen"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Ruth Bader Ginsburg", "textObjs": [{"text": "No.", "start": 2410.902, "stop": 2411.068, "duration": 0.17, "cleanText": [["no"]]}, {"text": "I would like to take this scenario as it is except that when the officer gets out of the car, his dog comes with him.", "start": 2411.068, "stop": 2418.294, "duration": 7.23, "cleanText": [["i", "would", "like", "to", "take", "this", "scenario", "as", "it", "be", "except", "that", "when", "the", "officer", "get", "out", "of", "the", "car", "his", "dog", "come", "with", "him"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Ralph E. Meczyk", "textObjs": [{"text": "Okay.", "start": 2418.294, "stop": 2420.595, "duration": 2.3, "cleanText": [["okay"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Ruth Bader Ginsburg", "textObjs": [{"text": "This is very... make no other changes except that Gillette has the dog and Gillette with the dog go to Mr. Caballes' car.", "start": 2420.595, "stop": 2430.133, "duration": 9.54, "cleanText": [["this", "be", "very", "make", "no", "other", "change", "except", "that", "gillette", "have", "the", "dog", "and", "gillette", "with", "the", "dog", "go", "to", "mr", "caballes", "car"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Ralph E. Meczyk", "textObjs": [{"text": "My understanding of the way this works, Justice Ginsburg, is that he just couldn't go up to the car without... and the dog would alert.", "start": 2430.133, "stop": 2438.594, "duration": 8.46, "cleanText": [["my", "understanding", "of", "the", "way", "this", "work", "justice", "ginsburg", "be", "that", "he", "just", "could", "not", "go", "up", "to", "the", "car", "without", "and", "the", "dog", "would", "alert"]]}, {"text": "My understanding of the way these dogs are trained is that they specifically... that the officer has to walk the dog around the car, the vehicle, first of all.", "start": 2438.594, "stop": 2448.253, "duration": 9.66, "cleanText": [["my", "understanding", "of", "the", "way", "these", "dog", "be", "train", "be", "that", "they", "specifically", "that", "the", "officer", "have", "to", "walk", "the", "dog", "around", "the", "car", "the", "vehicle", "first", "of", "all"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Antonin Scalia", "textObjs": [{"text": "He does that.", "start": 2448.253, "stop": 2448.83, "duration": 0.58, "cleanText": [["he", "do", "that"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Ralph E. Meczyk", "textObjs": [{"text": "He does that.", "start": 2448.83, "stop": 2449.452, "duration": 0.62, "cleanText": [["he", "do", "that"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Antonin Scalia", "textObjs": [{"text": "Yes, in this case.", "start": 2449.452, "stop": 2450.4, "duration": 0.95, "cleanText": [["yes", "in", "this", "case"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Ralph E. Meczyk", "textObjs": [{"text": "He does that.", "start": 2450.4, "stop": 2451.31, "duration": 0.91, "cleanText": [["he", "do", "that"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Antonin Scalia", "textObjs": [{"text": "Right.", "start": 2451.31, "stop": 2451.803, "duration": 0.49, "cleanText": [["right"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Ralph E. Meczyk", "textObjs": [{"text": "To cue the dog.", "start": 2451.803, "stop": 2452.629, "duration": 0.83, "cleanText": [["to", "cue", "the", "dog"]]}, {"text": "In other words, tell him it's not playtime anymore, that he has to work.", "start": 2452.629, "stop": 2455.868, "duration": 3.24, "cleanText": [["in", "other", "word", "tell", "him", "it", "be", "not", "playtime", "anymore", "that", "he", "have", "to", "work"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Antonin Scalia", "textObjs": [{"text": "Right.", "start": 2455.868, "stop": 2456.172, "duration": 0.3, "cleanText": [["right"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Ralph E. Meczyk", "textObjs": [{"text": "To trigger something in the... in the canine brain.", "start": 2456.172, "stop": 2458.113, "duration": 1.94, "cleanText": [["to", "trigger", "something", "in", "the", "in", "the", "canine", "brain"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Antonin Scalia", "textObjs": [{"text": "Right.", "start": 2458.113, "stop": 2458.568, "duration": 0.46, "cleanText": [["right"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Ruth Bader Ginsburg", "textObjs": [{"text": "But you... I'm--", "start": 2458.568, "stop": 2459.561, "duration": 0.99, "cleanText": [["but", "you"], ["I", "be"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Antonin Scalia", "textObjs": [{"text": "Would it be bad?", "start": 2459.561, "stop": 2459.894, "duration": 0.33, "cleanText": [["would", "it", "be", "bad"]]}, {"text": "Would it be bad if that's what he did?", "start": 2459.894, "stop": 2461.63, "duration": 1.74, "cleanText": [["would", "it", "be", "bad", "if", "that", "be", "what", "he", "do"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Ralph E. Meczyk", "textObjs": [{"text": "It wouldn't be bad that's what... well, yes.", "start": 2461.63, "stop": 2463.859, "duration": 2.23, "cleanText": [["it", "would", "not", "be", "bad", "that", "be", "what", "well", "yes"]]}, {"text": "In this case it's very bad because it's a search.", "start": 2463.859, "stop": 2466.21, "duration": 2.35, "cleanText": [["in", "this", "case", "it", "be", "very", "bad", "because", "it", "be", "a", "search"]]}, {"text": "There's no question.", "start": 2466.21, "stop": 2467.036, "duration": 0.83, "cleanText": [["there", "be", "no", "question"]]}, {"text": "I'm not coming off of that.", "start": 2467.036, "stop": 2468.029, "duration": 0.99, "cleanText": [["I", "be", "not", "come", "off", "of", "that"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Ruth Bader Ginsburg", "textObjs": [{"text": "--But I'm... I'm trying to understand what you meant in your brief when you said if the dog had been in Gillette's car when Gillette stopped Caballes, the situation would have been different.", "start": 2468.029, "stop": 2484.126, "duration": 16.1, "cleanText": [["but", "I", "be"], ["I", "be", "try", "to", "understand", "what", "you", "mean", "in", "your", "brief", "when", "you", "say", "if", "the", "dog", "have", "be", "in", "gillette", "s", "car", "when", "gillette", "stop", "caballes", "the", "situation", "would", "have", "be", "different"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Ralph E. Meczyk", "textObjs": [{"text": "I... I think what I meant there... there would have been... it would have been purely happenstance, almost like plain view.", "start": 2484.126, "stop": 2492.549, "duration": 8.42, "cleanText": [["i", "i", "think", "what", "i", "mean", "there", "there", "would", "have", "be", "it", "would", "have", "be", "purely", "happenstance", "almost", "like", "plain", "view"]]}, {"text": "It would have been... without him even cuing the dog or starting to walk the dog around, my answer to that Justice Ginsburg is that that would have been all right.", "start": 2492.549, "stop": 2501.382, "duration": 8.83, "cleanText": [["it", "would", "have", "be", "without", "him", "even", "cue", "the", "dog", "or", "start", "to", "walk", "the", "dog", "around", "my", "answer", "to", "that", "justice", "ginsburg", "be", "that", "that", "would", "have", "be", "all", "right"]]}, {"text": "Except now that... the more I think about it, I'm not so sure that it would be all right.", "start": 2501.382, "stop": 2506.296, "duration": 4.91, "cleanText": [["except", "now", "that", "the", "more", "i", "think", "about", "it", "I", "be", "not", "so", "sure", "that", "it", "would", "be", "all", "right"]]}, {"text": "And my answer to... and the reason for that is I think in that case the officer, if he could do such a thing and the dog would alert, would be exploiting the situation, would just be taking the dog and walking him around the car and seeing that the dog alerted.", "start": 2506.296, "stop": 2520.125, "duration": 13.83, "cleanText": [["and", "my", "answer", "to", "and", "the", "reason", "for", "that", "be", "i", "think", "in", "that", "case", "the", "officer", "if", "he", "could", "do", "such", "a", "thing", "and", "the", "dog", "would", "alert", "would", "be", "exploit", "the", "situation", "would", "just", "be", "take", "the", "dog", "and", "walk", "him", "around", "the", "car", "and", "seeing", "that", "the", "dog", "alert"]]}, {"text": "So in other words, there... there would be, I think, an exploitation of... of the... of the traffic stop.", "start": 2520.125, "stop": 2525.121, "duration": 5, "cleanText": [["so", "in", "other", "word", "there", "there", "would", "be", "i", "think", "an", "exploitation", "of", "of", "the", "of", "the", "traffic", "stop"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Ruth Bader Ginsburg", "textObjs": [{"text": "So then it really makes no difference whether it was Gillette who had the dog in his car or whether the dispatcher called another officer who had the dog.", "start": 2525.121, "stop": 2535.152, "duration": 10.03, "cleanText": [["so", "then", "it", "really", "make", "no", "difference", "whether", "it", "be", "gillette", "who", "have", "the", "dog", "in", "his", "car", "or", "whether", "the", "dispatcher", "call", "another", "officer", "who", "have", "the", "dog"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Ralph E. Meczyk", "textObjs": [{"text": "That is correct, Your Honor.", "start": 2535.152, "stop": 2536.228, "duration": 1.08, "cleanText": [["that", "be", "correct", "your", "honor"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Ruth Bader Ginsburg", "textObjs": [{"text": "It doesn't... so you're retracting that.", "start": 2536.228, "stop": 2539.572, "duration": 3.34, "cleanText": [["it", "do", "not", "so", "you", "be", "retract", "that"]]}, {"text": "You, I think, were asked but I'm... I'm not sure you fully answered.", "start": 2539.572, "stop": 2545.183, "duration": 5.61, "cleanText": [["you", "i", "think", "we", "be", "ask", "but", "I", "be"], ["I", "be", "not", "sure", "you", "fully", "answer"]]}, {"text": "Suppose the police, as Atwater would allow, arrested, made a full arrest of Caballes, and then they impound his car.", "start": 2545.183, "stop": 2557.776, "duration": 12.59, "cleanText": [["suppose", "the", "police", "as", "atwater", "would", "allow", "arrest", "make", "a", "full", "arrest", "of", "caballes", "and", "then", "they", "impound", "his", "car"]]}, {"text": "In the place where they put it, couldn't they have a dog go around the car there?", "start": 2557.776, "stop": 2566.526, "duration": 8.75, "cleanText": [["in", "the", "place", "where", "they", "put", "it", "could", "not", "they", "have", "a", "dog", "go", "around", "the", "car", "there"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Ralph E. Meczyk", "textObjs": [{"text": "Yes.", "start": 2566.526, "stop": 2568.383, "duration": 1.86, "cleanText": [["yes"]]}, {"text": "I... if we had an Atwater situation... in this case there wasn't an Atwater situation because there was first a warning given.", "start": 2568.383, "stop": 2578.414, "duration": 10.03, "cleanText": [["i", "if", "we", "have", "an", "atwater", "situation", "in", "this", "case", "there", "be", "not", "an", "atwater", "situation", "because", "there", "be", "first", "a", "warning", "give"]]}, {"text": "You're correct.", "start": 2578.414, "stop": 2579.363, "duration": 0.95, "cleanText": [["you", "be", "correct"]]}, {"text": "There was a warning given.", "start": 2579.363, "stop": 2581.22, "duration": 1.86, "cleanText": [["there", "be", "a", "warning", "give"]]}, {"text": "I'm sorry.", "start": 2581.22, "stop": 2582.129, "duration": 0.91, "cleanText": [["I", "be", "sorry"]]}, {"text": "The officer Gillette told Caballes he was going to give him a warning.", "start": 2582.129, "stop": 2584.936, "duration": 2.81, "cleanText": [["the", "officer", "gillette", "tell", "caballes", "he", "be", "go", "to", "give", "him", "a", "warning"]]}, {"text": "So unlike the Knowles--", "start": 2584.936, "stop": 2586.422, "duration": 1.49, "cleanText": [["so", "unlike", "the", "knowles"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Ruth Bader Ginsburg", "textObjs": [{"text": "But he could have.", "start": 2586.422, "stop": 2587.044, "duration": 0.62, "cleanText": [["but", "he", "could", "have"]]}, {"text": "He could have.", "start": 2587.044, "stop": 2587.991, "duration": 0.95, "cleanText": [["he", "could", "have"]]}, {"text": "I mean--", "start": 2587.991, "stop": 2588.446, "duration": 0.45, "cleanText": [["i", "mean"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Ralph E. Meczyk", "textObjs": [{"text": "--He could have, but he didn't.", "start": 2588.446, "stop": 2589.189, "duration": 0.74, "cleanText": [["he", "could", "have", "but", "he", "do", "not"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Ruth Bader Ginsburg", "textObjs": [{"text": "--is... is--", "start": 2589.189, "stop": 2589.932, "duration": 0.74, "cleanText": [["be", "be"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Ralph E. Meczyk", "textObjs": [{"text": "He didn't.", "start": 2589.932, "stop": 2591.584, "duration": 1.65, "cleanText": [["he", "do", "not"]]}, {"text": "Instead, he chose to treat this as more of a Knowles situation.", "start": 2591.584, "stop": 2596.785, "duration": 5.2, "cleanText": [["instead", "he", "choose", "to", "treat", "this", "as", "more", "of", "a", "knowles", "situation"]]}, {"text": "This case is... is on all fours, no pun intended, like Knowles.", "start": 2596.785, "stop": 2601.244, "duration": 4.46, "cleanText": [["this", "case", "be", "be", "on", "all", "four", "no", "pun", "intend", "like", "knowles"]]}, {"text": "In other words, in the... in Knowles v. Iowa, the Court... a case of this... I'm sorry.", "start": 2601.244, "stop": 2606.529, "duration": 5.28, "cleanText": [["in", "other", "word", "in", "the", "in", "knowles", "v", "iowa", "the", "court", "a", "case", "of", "this"], ["I", "be", "sorry"]]}, {"text": "Let me untwist my tongue.", "start": 2606.529, "stop": 2607.476, "duration": 0.95, "cleanText": [["let", "me", "untwist", "my", "tongue"]]}, {"text": "In Knowles v. Iowa, you had a... you had a traffic stop and after the traffic stop, there was a statute that said unrelated to the traffic stop, you can go in and search.", "start": 2607.476, "stop": 2617.219, "duration": 9.74, "cleanText": [["in", "knowles", "v", "iowa", "you", "have", "a", "you", "have", "a", "traffic", "stop", "and", "after", "the", "traffic", "stop", "there", "be", "a", "statute", "that", "say", "unrelated", "to", "the", "traffic", "stop", "you", "can", "go", "in", "and", "search"]]}, {"text": "And this is the same thing.", "start": 2617.219, "stop": 2619.737, "duration": 2.52, "cleanText": [["and", "this", "be", "the", "same", "thing"]]}, {"text": "This officer here Gillette treated Caballes as the officer in Knowles in... treated Mr. Knowles in Iowa.", "start": 2619.737, "stop": 2627.555, "duration": 7.82, "cleanText": [["this", "officer", "here", "gillette", "treated", "caballes", "as", "the", "officer", "in", "knowles", "in", "treat", "mr", "knowles", "in", "iowa"]]}, {"text": "It's the exact same thing.", "start": 2627.555, "stop": 2628.67, "duration": 1.12, "cleanText": [["it", "be", "the", "exact", "same", "thing"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "David H. Souter", "textObjs": [{"text": "No, but the... the difficulty that I have with that argument is take the... take the case of... of the arrestable offense in which it is undoubtedly the case that although the police don't normally arrest, they... they can.", "start": 2628.67, "stop": 2640.709, "duration": 12.04, "cleanText": [["no", "but", "the", "the", "difficulty", "that", "i", "have", "with", "that", "argument", "be", "take", "the", "take", "the", "case", "of", "of", "the", "arrestable", "offense", "in", "which", "it", "be", "undoubtedly", "the", "case", "that", "although", "the", "police", "do", "not", "normally", "arrest", "they", "they", "can"]]}, {"text": "Your... if I understand your argument, you're saying if they, in fact, do arrest, they may then take the dog around the car, and indeed, I presume you would agree, they could make an inventory search because they've got to protect themselves against claims that they lost property and so on.", "start": 2640.709, "stop": 2658.292, "duration": 17.58, "cleanText": [["your", "if", "i", "understand", "your", "argument", "you", "be", "say", "if", "they", "in", "fact", "do", "arrest", "they", "may", "then", "take", "the", "dog", "around", "the", "car", "and", "indeed", "i", "presume", "you", "would", "agree", "they", "could", "make", "an", "inventory", "search", "because", "they", "have", "get", "to", "protect", "themselves", "against", "claim", "that", "they", "lose", "property", "and", "so", "on"]]}, {"text": "So there's no question that in that case, as... as you have argued it, they could make a full-blown search and... and certainly can use the dog.", "start": 2658.292, "stop": 2667.951, "duration": 9.66, "cleanText": [["so", "there", "be", "no", "question", "that", "in", "that", "case", "as", "as", "you", "have", "argue", "it", "they", "could", "make", "a", "full", "blow", "search", "and", "and", "certainly", "can", "use", "the", "dog"]]}, {"text": "But if they choose not to arrest on the highway, they can't.", "start": 2667.951, "stop": 2671.666, "duration": 3.72, "cleanText": [["but", "if", "they", "choose", "not", "to", "arrest", "on", "the", "highway", "they", "can", "not"]]}, {"text": "My problem is how can you say that there is a reasonable expectation of privacy in case number two if you admit that the police can search in case number one.", "start": 2671.666, "stop": 2683.183, "duration": 11.52, "cleanText": [["my", "problem", "be", "how", "can", "you", "say", "that", "there", "be", "a", "reasonable", "expectation", "of", "privacy", "in", "case", "number", "two", "if", "you", "admit", "that", "the", "police", "can", "search", "in", "case", "number", "one"]]}, {"text": "How does that affect the reasonable expectation of privacy?", "start": 2683.183, "stop": 2687.642, "duration": 4.46, "cleanText": [["how", "do", "that", "affect", "the", "reasonable", "expectation", "of", "privacy"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Ralph E. Meczyk", "textObjs": [{"text": "To me, once a person is told that he is not going to be under arrest, it changes the whole complexion of the case.", "start": 2687.642, "stop": 2695.898, "duration": 8.26, "cleanText": [["to", "me", "once", "a", "person", "be", "tell", "that", "he", "be", "not", "go", "to", "be", "under", "arrest", "it", "change", "the", "whole", "complexion", "of", "the", "case"]]}, {"text": "I think it's a completely different... a completely different scenario.", "start": 2695.898, "stop": 2699.985, "duration": 4.09, "cleanText": [["i", "think", "it", "be", "a", "completely", "different", "a", "completely", "different", "scenario"]]}, {"text": "We don't have an arrest.", "start": 2699.985, "stop": 2701.721, "duration": 1.74, "cleanText": [["we", "do", "not", "have", "an", "arrest"]]}, {"text": "It doesn't matter.", "start": 2701.721, "stop": 2702.668, "duration": 0.95, "cleanText": [["it", "do", "not", "matter"]]}, {"text": "Atwater--", "start": 2702.668, "stop": 2703.595, "duration": 0.93, "cleanText": [["atwater"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Ruth Bader Ginsburg", "textObjs": [{"text": "--Could the officer change his mind?", "start": 2703.595, "stop": 2704.793, "duration": 1.2, "cleanText": [["could", "the", "officer", "change", "his", "mind"]]}, {"text": "I mean, he... he did say I'm just going to give you a citation, and then he said, mind if I search your car.", "start": 2704.793, "stop": 2711.275, "duration": 6.48, "cleanText": [["i", "mean", "he", "he", "do", "say", "I", "be", "just", "go", "to", "give", "you", "a", "citation", "and", "then", "he", "say", "mind", "if", "i", "search", "your", "car"]]}, {"text": "This is before the... the dog showed up.", "start": 2711.275, "stop": 2713.959, "duration": 2.68, "cleanText": [["this", "be", "before", "the", "the", "dog", "show", "up"]]}, {"text": "And suppose the person who had been speeding said, yes, I mind.", "start": 2713.959, "stop": 2719.903, "duration": 5.94, "cleanText": [["and", "suppose", "the", "person", "who", "have", "be", "speed", "say", "yes", "i", "mind"]]}, {"text": "Don't search my car.", "start": 2719.903, "stop": 2721.1, "duration": 1.2, "cleanText": [["do", "not", "search", "my", "car"]]}, {"text": "And then the police said, well, in that case I'm going to arrest you.", "start": 2721.1, "stop": 2725.476, "duration": 4.38, "cleanText": [["and", "then", "the", "police", "say", "well", "in", "that", "case", "I", "be", "go", "to", "arrest", "you"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Ralph E. Meczyk", "textObjs": [{"text": "--It's a difficult question, but I have to look at what... I think reasonableness is judged.", "start": 2725.476, "stop": 2734.309, "duration": 8.83, "cleanText": [["it", "be", "a", "difficult", "question", "but", "i", "have", "to", "look", "at", "what", "i", "think", "reasonableness", "be", "judge"]]}, {"text": "Again, I'm going to remember what the... those cases taught.", "start": 2734.309, "stop": 2738.396, "duration": 4.09, "cleanText": [["again", "I", "be", "go", "to", "remember", "what", "the", "those", "case", "teach"]]}, {"text": "I think what Knowles taught, that reasonableness is judged by what the police actually do as opposed to what they might have done.", "start": 2738.396, "stop": 2747.312, "duration": 8.92, "cleanText": [["i", "think", "what", "knowles", "taught", "that", "reasonableness", "be", "judge", "by", "what", "the", "police", "actually", "do", "as", "oppose", "to", "what", "they", "might", "have", "do"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Antonin Scalia", "textObjs": [{"text": "Mr. Meczyk, I assume that your answer to whether it's lawful to have a... a dog at a bus depot just to sniff the bags of people who were coming off, without stopping them, but just... just to have the dogs there, that's unlawful.", "start": 2747.312, "stop": 2769.482, "duration": 22.17, "cleanText": [["mr", "meczyk", "i", "assume", "that", "your", "answer", "to", "whether", "it", "be", "lawful", "to", "have", "a", "a", "dog", "at", "a", "bus", "depot", "just", "to", "sniff", "the", "bag", "of", "people", "who", "we", "be", "come", "off", "without", "stop", "them", "but", "just", "just", "to", "have", "the", "dog", "there", "that", "be", "unlawful"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Ralph E. Meczyk", "textObjs": [{"text": "It depends--", "start": 2769.482, "stop": 2773.03, "duration": 3.55, "cleanText": [["it", "depend"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Antonin Scalia", "textObjs": [{"text": "For narcotics, not for bombs, not for... just... just for narcotics.", "start": 2773.03, "stop": 2776.374, "duration": 3.34, "cleanText": [["for", "narcotic", "not", "for", "bomb", "not", "for", "just", "just", "for", "narcotic"]]}, {"text": "The police think, you know, a lot of narcotics goes on interstate buses.", "start": 2776.374, "stop": 2780.915, "duration": 4.54, "cleanText": [["the", "police", "think", "you", "know", "a", "lot", "of", "narcotic", "go", "on", "interstate", "bus"]]}, {"text": "We're going to put a dog in the bus depot.", "start": 2780.915, "stop": 2782.873, "duration": 1.96, "cleanText": [["we", "be", "go", "to", "put", "a", "dog", "in", "the", "bus", "depot"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Ralph E. Meczyk", "textObjs": [{"text": "--It's a little less problematic to me, Justice Scalia, than the type of stop I'm talking about here.", "start": 2782.873, "stop": 2789.089, "duration": 6.22, "cleanText": [["it", "be", "a", "little", "less", "problematic", "to", "me", "justice", "scalia", "than", "the", "type", "of", "stop", "I", "be", "talk", "about", "here"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Antonin Scalia", "textObjs": [{"text": "Why?", "start": 2789.089, "stop": 2789.56, "duration": 0.47, "cleanText": [["why"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Ralph E. Meczyk", "textObjs": [{"text": "It's a little less problematic.", "start": 2789.56, "stop": 2791.501, "duration": 1.94, "cleanText": [["it", "be", "a", "little", "less", "problematic"]]}, {"text": "One, because it's a public place and I... I think--", "start": 2791.501, "stop": 2795.504, "duration": 4, "cleanText": [["one", "because", "it", "be", "a", "public", "place", "and", "i", "i", "think"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Antonin Scalia", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, so is the road, for Pete's sake.", "start": 2795.504, "stop": 2796.785, "duration": 1.28, "cleanText": [["well", "so", "be", "the", "road", "for", "pete", "s", "sake"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Ralph E. Meczyk", "textObjs": [{"text": "--I know, but... but here I think there's a lesser expectation of privacy.", "start": 2796.785, "stop": 2800.666, "duration": 3.88, "cleanText": [["i", "know", "but", "but", "here", "i", "think", "there", "be", "a", "less", "expectation", "of", "privacy"]]}, {"text": "Well, I don't even want to go that far.", "start": 2800.666, "stop": 2802.441, "duration": 1.77, "cleanText": [["well", "i", "do", "not", "even", "want", "to", "go", "that", "far"]]}, {"text": "I... I have to answer your question.", "start": 2802.441, "stop": 2803.844, "duration": 1.4, "cleanText": [["i", "i", "have", "to", "answer", "your", "question"]]}, {"text": "I think that submitting the dogs without any... submitting the luggage without any reasonable articulable suspicion--", "start": 2803.844, "stop": 2811.357, "duration": 7.51, "cleanText": [["i", "think", "that", "submit", "the", "dog", "without", "any", "submit", "the", "luggage", "without", "any", "reasonable", "articulable", "suspicion"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Antonin Scalia", "textObjs": [{"text": "Right.", "start": 2811.357, "stop": 2811.812, "duration": 0.45, "cleanText": [["right"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Ralph E. Meczyk", "textObjs": [{"text": "--unlike the case--", "start": 2811.812, "stop": 2812.639, "duration": 0.83, "cleanText": [["unlike", "the", "case"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Antonin Scalia", "textObjs": [{"text": "Right.", "start": 2812.639, "stop": 2813.132, "duration": 0.49, "cleanText": [["right"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Ralph E. Meczyk", "textObjs": [{"text": "--unlike the case in... in Place, that that to me is still a search.", "start": 2813.132, "stop": 2817.18, "duration": 4.05, "cleanText": [["unlike", "the", "case", "in", "in", "place", "that", "that", "to", "me", "be", "still", "a", "search"]]}, {"text": "So--", "start": 2817.18, "stop": 2817.552, "duration": 0.37, "cleanText": [["so"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Antonin Scalia", "textObjs": [{"text": "Okay.", "start": 2817.552, "stop": 2817.885, "duration": 0.33, "cleanText": [["okay"]]}, {"text": "That's... that's what I think you should say.", "start": 2817.885, "stop": 2819.288, "duration": 1.4, "cleanText": [["that", "be", "that", "be", "what", "i", "think", "you", "should", "say"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Ralph E. Meczyk", "textObjs": [{"text": "--And I am saying it.", "start": 2819.288, "stop": 2820.031, "duration": 0.74, "cleanText": [["and", "i", "be", "say", "it"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Stephen G. Breyer", "textObjs": [{"text": "Yes, but that isn't... I take it you don't--", "start": 2820.031, "stop": 2822.798, "duration": 2.77, "cleanText": [["yes", "but", "that", "be", "not", "i", "take", "it", "you", "do", "not"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Ralph E. Meczyk", "textObjs": [{"text": "Sorry it took me so long.", "start": 2822.798, "stop": 2823.624, "duration": 0.83, "cleanText": [["sorry", "it", "take", "me", "so", "long"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Stephen G. Breyer", "textObjs": [{"text": "--Is there anything wrong with the policeman himself taking a sniff?", "start": 2823.624, "stop": 2828.082, "duration": 4.46, "cleanText": [["be", "there", "anything", "wrong", "with", "the", "policeman", "himself", "take", "a", "sniff"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Ralph E. Meczyk", "textObjs": [{"text": "It goes back to--", "start": 2828.082, "stop": 2830.106, "duration": 2.02, "cleanText": [["it", "go", "back", "to"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Stephen G. Breyer", "textObjs": [{"text": "It's the great Limburger cheese robbery.", "start": 2830.106, "stop": 2831.925, "duration": 1.82, "cleanText": [["it", "be", "the", "great", "limburger", "cheese", "robbery"]]}, {"text": "[Laughter]", "start": 2831.925, "stop": 2832.501, "duration": 0.58, "cleanText": [["laughter"]]}, {"text": "He stopped the car and he walks around.", "start": 2832.501, "stop": 2834.73, "duration": 2.23, "cleanText": [["he", "stop", "the", "car", "and", "he", "walk", "around"]]}, {"text": "Anything wrong with that?", "start": 2834.73, "stop": 2836.422, "duration": 1.69, "cleanText": [["anything", "wrong", "with", "that"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Ralph E. Meczyk", "textObjs": [{"text": "--There's nothing wrong if he can detect Limburger cheese.", "start": 2836.422, "stop": 2839.105, "duration": 2.68, "cleanText": [["there", "be", "nothing", "wrong", "if", "he", "can", "detect", "limburger", "cheese"]]}, {"text": "That to me is like plain smell.", "start": 2839.105, "stop": 2840.675, "duration": 1.57, "cleanText": [["that", "to", "me", "be", "like", "plain", "smell"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Stephen G. Breyer", "textObjs": [{"text": "All right.", "start": 2840.675, "stop": 2841.213, "duration": 0.54, "cleanText": [["all", "right"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Ralph E. Meczyk", "textObjs": [{"text": "As awful as that--", "start": 2841.213, "stop": 2842.122, "duration": 0.91, "cleanText": [["as", "awful", "as", "that"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Stephen G. Breyer", "textObjs": [{"text": "So plain--", "start": 2842.122, "stop": 2842.699, "duration": 0.58, "cleanText": [["so", "plain"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Ralph E. Meczyk", "textObjs": [{"text": "--As awful as it might be--", "start": 2842.699, "stop": 2843.814, "duration": 1.11, "cleanText": [["as", "awful", "as", "it", "might", "be"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Stephen G. Breyer", "textObjs": [{"text": "--All right.", "start": 2843.814, "stop": 2844.185, "duration": 0.37, "cleanText": [["all", "right"]]}, {"text": "So... so what you're saying is... and this must tie back to reasonable expectation of privacy.", "start": 2844.185, "stop": 2849.924, "duration": 5.74, "cleanText": [["so", "so", "what", "you", "be", "say", "be", "and", "this", "must", "tie", "back", "to", "reasonable", "expectation", "of", "privacy"]]}, {"text": "All right?", "start": 2849.924, "stop": 2850.584, "duration": 0.66, "cleanText": [["all", "right"]]}, {"text": "Because it's okay for the policeman to do it, and it's okay for dogs to do it in the bus station, and it's okay to use a dog not in the bus station with a car if in fact you actually are going to put him under arrest, although here you had probable cause to do so, I take it.", "start": 2850.584, "stop": 2868.128, "duration": 17.54, "cleanText": [["because", "it", "be", "okay", "for", "the", "policeman", "to", "do", "it", "and", "it", "be", "okay", "for", "dog", "to", "do", "it", "in", "the", "bus", "station", "and", "it", "be", "okay", "to", "use", "a", "dog", "not", "in", "the", "bus", "station", "with", "a", "car", "if", "in", "fact", "you", "actually", "be", "go", "to", "put", "him", "under", "arrest", "although", "here", "you", "have", "probable", "because", "to", "do", "so", "i", "take", "it"]]}, {"text": "And now you have to draw a pretty fine line.", "start": 2868.128, "stop": 2870.646, "duration": 2.52, "cleanText": [["and", "now", "you", "have", "to", "draw", "a", "pretty", "fine", "line"]]}, {"text": "But it's not okay where it's not the bus station, but it is the car and in fact the dog is doing the sniffing... and there are a lot of dogs around that can sniff... and you did have probable cause but you didn't say it.", "start": 2870.646, "stop": 2884.188, "duration": 13.54, "cleanText": [["but", "it", "be", "not", "okay", "where", "it", "be", "not", "the", "bus", "station", "but", "it", "be", "the", "car", "and", "in", "fact", "the", "dog", "be", "do", "the", "sniffing", "and", "there", "be", "a", "lot", "of", "dog", "around", "that", "can", "sniff", "and", "you", "do", "have", "probable", "because", "but", "you", "do", "not", "say", "it"]]}, {"text": "And in face of Justice O'Connor's case which said that... you see.", "start": 2884.188, "stop": 2889.76, "duration": 5.57, "cleanText": [["and", "in", "face", "of", "justice", "oconnor", "s", "case", "which", "say", "that", "you", "see"]]}, {"text": "Well, I mean, this is... this is--", "start": 2889.76, "stop": 2890.753, "duration": 0.99, "cleanText": [["well", "i", "mean", "this", "be", "this", "be"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Ralph E. Meczyk", "textObjs": [{"text": "--I guess you--", "start": 2890.753, "stop": 2891.329, "duration": 0.58, "cleanText": [["i", "guess", "you"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Stephen G. Breyer", "textObjs": [{"text": "--I mean, I'm not saying you couldn't draw that line, but I'm saying it's pretty tough I think.", "start": 2891.329, "stop": 2895.21, "duration": 3.88, "cleanText": [["i", "mean", "I", "be", "not", "say", "you", "could", "not", "draw", "that", "line", "but", "I", "be", "say", "it", "be", "pretty", "tough", "i", "think"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Ralph E. Meczyk", "textObjs": [{"text": "--I guess you're telling me I'm... I'm the underdog in this case.", "start": 2895.21, "stop": 2897.523, "duration": 2.31, "cleanText": [["i", "guess", "you", "be", "tell", "me", "I", "be"], ["I", "be", "the", "underdog", "in", "this", "case"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Stephen G. Breyer", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, I don't know.", "start": 2897.523, "stop": 2898.182, "duration": 0.66, "cleanText": [["well", "i", "do", "not", "know"]]}, {"text": "[Laughter]", "start": 2898.182, "stop": 2899.009, "duration": 0.83, "cleanText": [["laughter"]]}, {"text": "I'm right?", "start": 2899.009, "stop": 2900.595, "duration": 1.59, "cleanText": [["I", "be", "right"]]}, {"text": "Am I... I mean, that--", "start": 2900.595, "stop": 2901.71, "duration": 1.12, "cleanText": [["be", "i", "i", "mean", "that"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Ralph E. Meczyk", "textObjs": [{"text": "It is--", "start": 2901.71, "stop": 2902.081, "duration": 0.37, "cleanText": [["it", "be"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Stephen G. Breyer", "textObjs": [{"text": "--And you're going to draw the... well, I don't want you to repeat yourself necessarily.", "start": 2902.081, "stop": 2904.31, "duration": 2.23, "cleanText": [["and", "you", "be", "go", "to", "draw", "the", "well", "i", "do", "not", "want", "you", "to", "repeat", "yourself", "necessarily"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Ralph E. Meczyk", "textObjs": [{"text": "--No.", "start": 2904.31, "stop": 2904.476, "duration": 0.17, "cleanText": [["no"]]}, {"text": "It--", "start": 2904.476, "stop": 2904.809, "duration": 0.33, "cleanText": [["it"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Ruth Bader Ginsburg", "textObjs": [{"text": "But you had already drawn the line at a different place than Justice Breyer suggested because in response to Justice Scalia, you said if it... if it were going into the bus terminal just to sniff for narcotics, unlike explosives, it would be an impermissible search.", "start": 2904.809, "stop": 2923.302, "duration": 18.49, "cleanText": [["but", "you", "have", "already", "draw", "the", "line", "at", "a", "different", "place", "than", "justice", "breyer", "suggest", "because", "in", "response", "to", "justice", "scalia", "you", "say", "if", "it", "if", "it", "we", "be", "go", "into", "the", "bus", "terminal", "just", "to", "sniff", "for", "narcotic", "unlike", "explosive", "it", "would", "be", "an", "impermissible", "search"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Ralph E. Meczyk", "textObjs": [{"text": "--Yes, correct, Justice--", "start": 2923.302, "stop": 2923.924, "duration": 0.62, "cleanText": [["yes", "correct", "justice"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Ruth Bader Ginsburg", "textObjs": [{"text": "That would be--", "start": 2923.924, "stop": 2924.417, "duration": 0.49, "cleanText": [["that", "would", "be"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Ralph E. Meczyk", "textObjs": [{"text": "--That is correct, Justice Ginsburg.", "start": 2924.417, "stop": 2925.614, "duration": 1.2, "cleanText": [["that", "be", "correct", "justice", "ginsburg"]]}, {"text": "What makes this particular so--", "start": 2925.614, "stop": 2927.35, "duration": 1.74, "cleanText": [["what", "make", "this", "particular", "so"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "David H. Souter", "textObjs": [{"text": "But... but is... why... why don't you simply say, look... have a very simple line.", "start": 2927.35, "stop": 2931.353, "duration": 4, "cleanText": [["but", "but", "be", "why", "why", "do", "not", "you", "simply", "say", "look", "have", "a", "very", "simple", "line"]]}, {"text": "If they can arrest, they can sniff.", "start": 2931.353, "stop": 2932.923, "duration": 1.57, "cleanText": [["if", "they", "can", "arrest", "they", "can", "sniff"]]}, {"text": "If they can't arrest, they can't sniff without individualized suspicion going to drugs or whatever.", "start": 2932.923, "stop": 2938.617, "duration": 5.69, "cleanText": [["if", "they", "can", "not", "arrest", "they", "can", "not", "sniff", "without", "individualized", "suspicion", "go", "to", "drug", "or", "whatever"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Ralph E. Meczyk", "textObjs": [{"text": "--I would agree with that if I use an... if... if you're referring to an Atwater type scenario.", "start": 2938.617, "stop": 2944.561, "duration": 5.94, "cleanText": [["i", "would", "agree", "with", "that", "if", "i", "use", "an", "if", "if", "you", "be", "refer", "to", "an", "atwater", "type", "scenario"]]}, {"text": "If they have probable... if they decide to arrest, even though it's on a minor traffic case, such as Atwater, which was a seat belt, as long as it's... if... if it's minor and if the officer elects to choose to do a full-blown arrest, then all the consequences that follow from that arrest are... it's going to happen.", "start": 2944.561, "stop": 2963.675, "duration": 19.11, "cleanText": [["if", "they", "have", "probable", "if", "they", "decide", "to", "arrest", "even", "though", "it", "be", "on", "a", "minor", "traffic", "case", "such", "as", "atwater", "which", "be", "a", "seat", "belt", "as", "long", "as", "it", "be", "if", "if", "it", "be", "minor", "and", "if", "the", "officer", "elect", "to", "choose", "to", "do", "a", "full", "blown", "arrest", "then", "all", "the", "consequence", "that", "follow", "from", "that", "arrest", "be", "it", "be", "go", "to", "happen"]]}, {"text": "Excuse me.", "start": 2963.675, "stop": 2963.963, "duration": 0.29, "cleanText": [["excuse", "me"]]}, {"text": "It's going to happen.", "start": 2963.963, "stop": 2964.624, "duration": 0.66, "cleanText": [["it", "be", "go", "to", "happen"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "David H. Souter", "textObjs": [{"text": "But what... what is the answer to the reasonable expectation to privacy question in that case?", "start": 2964.624, "stop": 2970.279, "duration": 5.66, "cleanText": [["but", "what", "what", "be", "the", "answer", "to", "the", "reasonable", "expectation", "to", "privacy", "question", "in", "that", "case"]]}, {"text": "Isn't your expectation of privacy identical, whatever it may be, or isn't the reasonable expectation of privacy identical, whatever that may be, without regard to the discretionary decision of the officer to arrest or not?", "start": 2970.279, "stop": 2985.429, "duration": 15.15, "cleanText": [["be", "not", "your", "expectation", "of", "privacy", "identical", "whatever", "it", "may", "be", "or", "be", "not", "the", "reasonable", "expectation", "of", "privacy", "identical", "whatever", "that", "may", "be", "without", "regard", "to", "the", "discretionary", "decision", "of", "the", "officer", "to", "arrest", "or", "not"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Ralph E. Meczyk", "textObjs": [{"text": "I... I think that when the officer does a full-blown arrest, as was envisioned in Atwater, you know that you... the person knows that he or she does not have a reasonable expectation of privacy.", "start": 2985.429, "stop": 2998.227, "duration": 12.8, "cleanText": [["i", "i", "think", "that", "when", "the", "officer", "do", "a", "full", "blown", "arrest", "as", "be", "envision", "in", "atwater", "you", "know", "that", "you", "the", "person", "know", "that", "he", "or", "she", "do", "not", "have", "a", "reasonable", "expectation", "of", "privacy"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "David H. Souter", "textObjs": [{"text": "But you're saying that the... the reasonable expectation of privacy depends upon the officer's discretionary judgment whether or not to arrest.", "start": 2998.227, "stop": 3004.709, "duration": 6.48, "cleanText": [["but", "you", "be", "say", "that", "the", "the", "reasonable", "expectation", "of", "privacy", "depend", "upon", "the", "officer", "s", "discretionary", "judgment", "whether", "or", "not", "to", "arrest"]]}, {"text": "Isn't that what you're saying?", "start": 3004.709, "stop": 3006.855, "duration": 2.15, "cleanText": [["be", "not", "that", "what", "you", "be", "say"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Ralph E. Meczyk", "textObjs": [{"text": "Essentially yes, because I think that the officer takes a physical action.", "start": 3006.855, "stop": 3010.942, "duration": 4.09, "cleanText": [["essentially", "yes", "because", "i", "think", "that", "the", "officer", "take", "a", "physical", "action"]]}, {"text": "It's just more than words.", "start": 3010.942, "stop": 3012.595, "duration": 1.65, "cleanText": [["it", "be", "just", "more", "than", "word"]]}, {"text": "It's also his deeds.", "start": 3012.595, "stop": 3013.709, "duration": 1.11, "cleanText": [["it", "be", "also", "his", "deed"]]}, {"text": "I think in Atwater, unlike Knowles... in Atwater, in that case, I think the... the officer did make an election, and there was a full-blown or a full-fledged arrest.", "start": 3013.709, "stop": 3024.499, "duration": 10.79, "cleanText": [["i", "think", "in", "atwater", "unlike", "knowles", "in", "atwater", "in", "that", "case", "i", "think", "the", "the", "officer", "do", "make", "an", "election", "and", "there", "be", "a", "full", "blown", "or", "a", "full", "fledge", "arrest"]]}, {"text": "And I think there your... your reasonable expectation to privacy does, in fact, go out the window.", "start": 3024.499, "stop": 3029.806, "duration": 5.31, "cleanText": [["and", "i", "think", "there", "your", "your", "reasonable", "expectation", "to", "privacy", "do", "in", "fact", "go", "out", "the", "window"]]}, {"text": "But this is so different.", "start": 3029.806, "stop": 3031.375, "duration": 1.57, "cleanText": [["but", "this", "be", "so", "different"]]}, {"text": "This was just a warning.", "start": 3031.375, "stop": 3033.521, "duration": 2.15, "cleanText": [["this", "be", "just", "a", "warning"]]}, {"text": "Period.", "start": 3033.521, "stop": 3033.976, "duration": 0.45, "cleanText": [["period"]]}, {"text": "It was nothing worse than a warning.", "start": 3033.976, "stop": 3036.288, "duration": 2.31, "cleanText": [["it", "be", "nothing", "bad", "than", "a", "warning"]]}, {"text": "What makes this stop so pernicious is that it takes place in front of the whole world and is accusatory.", "start": 3036.288, "stop": 3044.173, "duration": 7.88, "cleanText": [["what", "make", "this", "stop", "so", "pernicious", "be", "that", "it", "take", "place", "in", "front", "of", "the", "whole", "world", "and", "be", "accusatory"]]}, {"text": "It is profoundly embarrassing, and it is humiliating to everyone on the street.", "start": 3044.173, "stop": 3050.777, "duration": 6.6, "cleanText": [["it", "be", "profoundly", "embarrassing", "and", "it", "be", "humiliate", "to", "everyone", "on", "the", "street"]]}, {"text": "So if a person is stopped and the officer just decides to stop you for a minor traffic offense, that's the worst part about this case.", "start": 3050.777, "stop": 3059.201, "duration": 8.42, "cleanText": [["so", "if", "a", "person", "be", "stop", "and", "the", "officer", "just", "decide", "to", "stop", "you", "for", "a", "minor", "traffic", "offense", "that", "be", "the", "bad", "part", "about", "this", "case"]]}, {"text": "Just a minor traffic offense, really a frivolous offense, basically what any law-abiding citizen would happen to... it could happen to anyone.", "start": 3059.201, "stop": 3067.29, "duration": 8.09, "cleanText": [["just", "a", "minor", "traffic", "offense", "really", "a", "frivolous", "offense", "basically", "what", "any", "law", "abide", "citizen", "would", "happen", "to", "it", "could", "happen", "to", "anyone"]]}, {"text": "And as this Court has said, even in Whren, there are so many multiple technical violations of... of... technical violations--", "start": 3067.29, "stop": 3074.926, "duration": 7.64, "cleanText": [["and", "as", "this", "court", "have", "say", "even", "in", "whren", "there", "be", "so", "many", "multiple", "technical", "violation", "of", "of", "technical", "violation"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Antonin Scalia", "textObjs": [{"text": "I mean, I think it's worse if... if you're subjected to it without having committed any violation at all.", "start": 3074.926, "stop": 3082.811, "duration": 7.89, "cleanText": [["i", "mean", "i", "think", "it", "be", "bad", "if", "if", "you", "be", "subject", "to", "it", "without", "have", "commit", "any", "violation", "at", "all"]]}, {"text": "Every time I travel abroad and come back into the country, customs officers have dogs and... and they parade the dogs through... through the baggage terminal.", "start": 3082.811, "stop": 3096.353, "duration": 13.54, "cleanText": [["every", "time", "i", "travel", "abroad", "and", "come", "back", "into", "the", "country", "custom", "officer", "have", "dog", "and", "and", "they", "parade", "the", "dog", "through", "through", "the", "baggage", "terminal"]]}, {"text": "Do... do I feel offended by that?", "start": 3096.353, "stop": 3100.272, "duration": 3.92, "cleanText": [["do", "do", "i", "feel", "offend", "by", "that"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Ralph E. Meczyk", "textObjs": [{"text": "--No, Justice Scalia--", "start": 3100.272, "stop": 3101.098, "duration": 0.83, "cleanText": [["no", "justice", "scalia"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Antonin Scalia", "textObjs": [{"text": "This isn't a public safety matter.", "start": 3101.098, "stop": 3102.75, "duration": 1.65, "cleanText": [["this", "be", "not", "a", "public", "safety", "matter"]]}, {"text": "They're... they're not smelling for bombs.", "start": 3102.75, "stop": 3104.813, "duration": 2.06, "cleanText": [["they", "be", "they", "be", "not", "smell", "for", "bomb"]]}, {"text": "They're... they're smelling for contraband.", "start": 3104.813, "stop": 3107.208, "duration": 2.39, "cleanText": [["they", "be", "they", "be", "smell", "for", "contraband"]]}, {"text": "And according to you, that is bad.", "start": 3107.208, "stop": 3109.437, "duration": 2.23, "cleanText": [["and", "accord", "to", "you", "that", "be", "bad"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Ralph E. Meczyk", "textObjs": [{"text": "--That... in that situation, when you enter the country... and this Court has said many times again... it's a border search.", "start": 3109.437, "stop": 3115.549, "duration": 6.11, "cleanText": [["that", "in", "that", "situation", "when", "you", "enter", "the", "country", "and", "this", "court", "have", "say", "many", "time", "again", "it", "be", "a", "border", "search"]]}, {"text": "There's nothing that I can argue against the border search.", "start": 3115.549, "stop": 3117.695, "duration": 2.15, "cleanText": [["there", "be", "nothing", "that", "i", "can", "argue", "against", "the", "border", "search"]]}, {"text": "It's the... or the functional equivalent of the border.", "start": 3117.695, "stop": 3120.045, "duration": 2.35, "cleanText": [["it", "be", "the", "or", "the", "functional", "equivalent", "of", "the", "border"]]}, {"text": "That is a border search.", "start": 3120.045, "stop": 3121.41, "duration": 1.36, "cleanText": [["that", "be", "a", "border", "search"]]}, {"text": "I bring luggage to the airport, in today's world I have a lesser expectation of privacy.", "start": 3121.41, "stop": 3125.868, "duration": 4.46, "cleanText": [["i", "bring", "luggage", "to", "the", "airport", "in", "today", "s", "world", "i", "have", "a", "less", "expectation", "of", "privacy"]]}, {"text": "If I know I'm traveling abroad and coming into the United States, that's different.", "start": 3125.868, "stop": 3129.705, "duration": 3.84, "cleanText": [["if", "i", "know", "I", "be", "travel", "abroad", "and", "come", "into", "the", "united", "state", "that", "be", "different"]]}, {"text": "That's different in an airport.", "start": 3129.705, "stop": 3130.82, "duration": 1.12, "cleanText": [["that", "be", "different", "in", "an", "airport"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Antonin Scalia", "textObjs": [{"text": "Okay.", "start": 3130.82, "stop": 3131.646, "duration": 0.83, "cleanText": [["okay"]]}, {"text": "A bus station is different, though.", "start": 3131.646, "stop": 3133.132, "duration": 1.49, "cleanText": [["a", "bus", "station", "be", "different", "though"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Ralph E. Meczyk", "textObjs": [{"text": "A bus station here inside the United States is different I think.", "start": 3133.132, "stop": 3136.354, "duration": 3.22, "cleanText": [["a", "bus", "station", "here", "inside", "the", "united", "state", "be", "different", "i", "think"]]}, {"text": "I... I look at your airport hypothetical as being... as dealing with a border.", "start": 3136.354, "stop": 3140.812, "duration": 4.46, "cleanText": [["i", "i", "look", "at", "your", "airport", "hypothetical", "as", "be", "as", "deal", "with", "a", "border"]]}, {"text": "If it's not at a border and I use your hypothetical, it's at O'Hare Airport or Reagan International Airport and they bring a dog up to sniff for drugs at the carousel, that to me is a search.", "start": 3140.812, "stop": 3151.253, "duration": 10.44, "cleanText": [["if", "it", "be", "not", "at", "a", "border", "and", "i", "use", "your", "hypothetical", "it", "be", "at", "ohare", "airport", "or", "reagan", "international", "airport", "and", "they", "bring", "a", "dog", "up", "to", "sniff", "for", "drug", "at", "the", "carousel", "that", "to", "me", "be", "a", "search"]]}, {"text": "It's like... I think you said in one opinion once if it... you used the duck analogy, well, if it walks like a duck or quacks like a duck.", "start": 3151.253, "stop": 3158.19, "duration": 6.94, "cleanText": [["it", "be", "like", "i", "think", "you", "say", "in", "one", "opinion", "once", "if", "it", "you", "use", "the", "duck", "analogy", "well", "if", "it", "walk", "like", "a", "duck", "or", "quack", "like", "a", "duck"]]}, {"text": "Here it's still a search.", "start": 3158.19, "stop": 3160.42, "duration": 2.23, "cleanText": [["here", "it", "be", "still", "a", "search"]]}, {"text": "It walks like a... a dog and it acts like a dog, but its specific function is in fact to search out in public and humiliate people.", "start": 3160.42, "stop": 3169.336, "duration": 8.92, "cleanText": [["it", "walk", "like", "a", "a", "dog", "and", "it", "act", "like", "a", "dog", "but", "its", "specific", "function", "be", "in", "fact", "to", "search", "out", "in", "public", "and", "humiliate", "people"]]}, {"text": "If there are any further questions.", "start": 3169.336, "stop": 3173.794, "duration": 4.46, "cleanText": [["if", "there", "be", "any", "further", "question"]]}, {"text": "I respectfully ask this honorable Court to affirm the wise judgment of the Illinois Supreme Court.", "start": 3173.794, "stop": 3179.572, "duration": 5.78, "cleanText": [["i", "respectfully", "ask", "this", "honorable", "court", "to", "affirm", "the", "wise", "judgment", "of", "the", "illinois", "supreme", "court"]]}, {"text": "Thank you.", "start": 3179.572, "stop": 3180.026, "duration": 0.45, "cleanText": [["thank", "you"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "John Paul Stevens", "textObjs": [{"text": "Thank you, Mr. Meczyk.", "start": 3180.026, "stop": 3181.346, "duration": 1.32, "cleanText": [["thank", "you", "mr", "meczyk"]]}, {"text": "General Madigan, you have I think about 3 minutes left.", "start": 3181.346, "stop": 3185.887, "duration": 4.54, "cleanText": [["general", "madigan", "you", "have", "i", "think", "about", "minute", "leave"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Lisa Madigan", "textObjs": [{"text": "Thank you, Justice Stevens.", "start": 3185.887, "stop": 3188.034, "duration": 2.15, "cleanText": [["thank", "you", "justice", "stevens"]]}, {"text": "Let me make three brief points.", "start": 3188.034, "stop": 3190.634, "duration": 2.6, "cleanText": [["let", "me", "make", "three", "brief", "point"]]}, {"text": "Number one, Justice Ginsburg asked a question about something that was in the respondent's brief, whether or not it made a difference if a dog was with Master Sergeant Gillette when he initiated the stop or if the dog was later brought, as was the case here, by Trooper Graham.", "start": 3190.634, "stop": 3212.061, "duration": 21.43, "cleanText": [["number", "one", "justice", "ginsburg", "ask", "a", "question", "about", "something", "that", "be", "in", "the", "respondent", "s", "brief", "whether", "or", "not", "it", "make", "a", "difference", "if", "a", "dog", "be", "with", "master", "sergeant", "gillette", "when", "he", "initiate", "the", "stop", "or", "if", "the", "dog", "be", "later", "bring", "as", "be", "the", "case", "here", "by", "trooper", "graham"]]}, {"text": "Really what Mr. Caballes is arguing for here is an inadvertence requirement which this Court very clearly held in Horton, there is no such requirement of inadvertence.", "start": 3212.061, "stop": 3225.451, "duration": 13.39, "cleanText": [["really", "what", "mr", "caballes", "be", "argue", "for", "here", "be", "an", "inadvertence", "requirement", "which", "this", "court", "very", "clearly", "hold", "in", "horton", "there", "be", "no", "such", "requirement", "of", "inadvertence"]]}, {"text": "And so a law officer, if they are at a lawful vantage point, do have the ability to detect incriminating facts.", "start": 3225.451, "stop": 3234.352, "duration": 8.9, "cleanText": [["and", "so", "a", "law", "officer", "if", "they", "be", "at", "a", "lawful", "vantage", "point", "do", "have", "the", "ability", "to", "detect", "incriminating", "fact"]]}, {"text": "That is not something that has to occur inadvertently.", "start": 3234.352, "stop": 3237.696, "duration": 3.34, "cleanText": [["that", "be", "not", "something", "that", "have", "to", "occur", "inadvertently"]]}, {"text": "It can happen intentionally.", "start": 3237.696, "stop": 3239.182, "duration": 1.49, "cleanText": [["it", "can", "happen", "intentionally"]]}, {"text": "Second, Justice Scalia asked a question about plain view, and similar to plain view, a dog sniff does not effect an incremental search or seizure.", "start": 3239.182, "stop": 3250.449, "duration": 11.27, "cleanText": [["second", "justice", "scalia", "ask", "a", "question", "about", "plain", "view", "and", "similar", "to", "plain", "view", "a", "dog", "sniff", "do", "not", "effect", "an", "incremental", "search", "or", "seizure"]]}, {"text": "And therefore, similar to plain view, a dog sniff does not require Fourth Amendment justification.", "start": 3250.449, "stop": 3257.508, "duration": 7.06, "cleanText": [["and", "therefore", "similar", "to", "plain", "view", "a", "dog", "sniff", "do", "not", "require", "fourth", "amendment", "justification"]]}, {"text": "And let me finally acknowledge something that Justice Souter brought up, which is whether or not, by walking a dog around a house, you in fact would have a search.", "start": 3257.508, "stop": 3271.625, "duration": 14.12, "cleanText": [["and", "let", "me", "finally", "acknowledge", "something", "that", "justice", "souter", "bring", "up", "which", "be", "whether", "or", "not", "by", "walk", "a", "dog", "around", "a", "house", "you", "in", "fact", "would", "have", "a", "search"]]}, {"text": "Let me... now, that is certainly a closer case than whether walking a dog around a car constitutes a search, which we say is not.", "start": 3271.625, "stop": 3279.593, "duration": 7.97, "cleanText": [["let", "me", "now", "that", "be", "certainly", "a", "close", "case", "than", "whether", "walk", "a", "dog", "around", "a", "car", "constitute", "a", "search", "which", "we", "say", "be", "not"]]}, {"text": "But ultimately you would reach a similar result because the principle is not going to extend to cars in the same manner in... in Kyllo as the thermal imager did.", "start": 3279.593, "stop": 3293.339, "duration": 13.75, "cleanText": [["but", "ultimately", "you", "would", "reach", "a", "similar", "result", "because", "the", "principle", "be", "not", "go", "to", "extend", "to", "car", "in", "the", "same", "manner", "in", "in", "kyllo", "as", "the", "thermal", "imager", "do"]]}, {"text": "Finally, if there are no further questions, we would ask that the judgment of the Illinois Supreme Court be reversed.", "start": 3293.339, "stop": 3300.565, "duration": 7.23, "cleanText": [["finally", "if", "there", "be", "no", "further", "question", "we", "would", "ask", "that", "the", "judgment", "of", "the", "illinois", "supreme", "court", "be", "reverse"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "John Paul Stevens", "textObjs": [{"text": "Thank you, General Madigan.", "start": 3300.565, "stop": 3302.09, "duration": 1.53, "cleanText": [["thank", "you", "general", "madigan"]]}, {"text": "The... the case is submitted.", "start": 3302.09, "stop": 3303.742, "duration": 1.65, "cleanText": [["the", "the", "case", "be", "submit"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Lisa Madigan", "textObjs": [{"text": "Thank you.", "start": 3303.742, "stop": 3304.319, "duration": 0.58, "cleanText": [["thank", "you"]]}]}]}], "decidedBy": "Rehnquist Court", "arguedOn": "Nov 10, 2004", "petitioner": "Illinois", "respondent": "Roy I. Caballes", "docket": "03-923", "citation": "543US405(2005)", "justiaLink": "https://supreme.justia.com/cases/federal/us/543/405", "lowerCourt": "Supreme Court of Illinois", "grantedOn": "Apr 5, 2004", "decidedOn": "Jan 24, 2005", "wikiData": {"title": "Illinois v. Caballes", "Litigants": "Illinois v. Caballes", "ArgueDate": "November 10", "ArgueYear": "2004", "DecideDate": "January 24", "DecideYear": "2005", "FullName": "Illinois, Petitioner v. Roy I. Caballes", "USVol": "543", "USPage": "405", "ParallelCitations": "125 S. Ct. 834; 160 [[L. Ed. 2d]] 842; 2005 [[U.S. LEXIS]] 769; 73 U.S.L.W. 4111; 18 Fla. L. Weekly Fed. S 100", "Prior": "On writ of certiorari to the Supreme Court of Illinois, ''People v. Caballes'', 207 Ill. 2d 504, 802 [[N.E.2d]] 202, 280 Ill. Dec. 277, 2003 Ill. LEXIS 2280 (2003)", "Subsequent": "", "Holding": "A dog sniff conducted during a concededly lawful traffic stop that reveals no information other than the location of a substance that no individual has any right to possess does not violate the Fourth Amendment.", "SCOTUS": "1994-2005", "Majority": "Stevens", "JoinMajority": "O'Connor, Scalia, Kennedy, Thomas, Breyer", "Dissent": "Souter", "Dissent2": "Ginsburg", "JoinDissent2": "Souter", "NotParticipating": "Rehnquist", "LawsApplied": "[[Fourth Amendment to the United States Constitution|U.S. Const. amend. IV]]"}}